WEBVTT

00:05.000 --> 00:08.542
♪ (intriguing music)

00:08.542 --> 00:17.917
♪

00:17.917 --> 00:20.375
We should get T-shirts
that say, "I survived

00:20.375 --> 00:25.000
a marathon seminar on
accelerator clauses."

00:25.000 --> 00:28.417
Correction. "barely survived."

00:28.417 --> 00:32.375
Can you believe it's
almost time for the dinner?

00:32.375 --> 00:35.583
No, no please. No
more real estate talk. -So?

00:35.583 --> 00:42.750
I suggest we skip dinner. Or at
least skip dinner with them.

00:42.750 --> 00:44.125
What are you thinking?

00:44.125 --> 00:46.917
The bar. A drink.

00:46.917 --> 00:47.917
More than one drink.

00:47.917 --> 00:56.375
♪

00:56.375 --> 00:58.042
Woman: Phone, dessert.
Phone, dessert

00:58.042 --> 00:59.500
Take your pick.

01:00.458 --> 01:01.292
Thank you.

01:03.250 --> 01:05.208
I'm losing you soon
enough when you graduate,

01:05.208 --> 01:07.542
I don't need you in a "phone
haze" with me right now.

01:07.542 --> 01:12.417
All right. My mind is clear
and focused on my birthday.

01:12.417 --> 01:15.542
(laughs) Well, good
because I need to know

01:15.542 --> 01:18.000
where you want to go for
your birthday dinner.

01:18.000 --> 01:19.042
Anywhere you want.

01:19.042 --> 01:20.375
How about Michael's?

01:20.375 --> 01:22.958
Well, that's
easy. Done!

01:22.958 --> 01:25.083
Ah, this.

01:25.083 --> 01:27.375
this house is going to
feel so empty without you.

01:27.375 --> 01:29.250
I mean, especially when
I'm not around to referee

01:29.250 --> 01:31.250
when you and Dad start arguing.

01:31.250 --> 01:34.917
Hey. I don't want you to
feel like you're in the middle.

01:34.917 --> 01:36.583
You know we both love you.

01:36.583 --> 01:38.792
♪

01:38.792 --> 01:40.292
Maybe once I'm out of the house,

01:40.292 --> 01:43.458
it'll give you and Dad a
chance to work on things,

01:43.458 --> 01:46.667
Yeah. I hope so.

01:46.667 --> 01:52.042
♪

01:52.042 --> 01:56.333
(siren blaring)

02:08.583 --> 02:10.875
(camera clicking)

02:32.708 --> 02:35.375
(sigh)

02:35.375 --> 02:37.125
Hey.

02:37.125 --> 02:38.583
What did we just do?

02:41.833 --> 02:44.708
(exhale)

02:44.708 --> 02:47.083
Something that's got
me feeling very guilty.

02:47.083 --> 02:49.750
-Same.

02:49.750 --> 02:52.375
So no one can ever know.

02:52.375 --> 02:54.708
Yeah, I... I understand.

02:54.708 --> 02:57.875
Believe me, Amy, this
stays between us.

02:59.750 --> 03:05.875
(exhale) Amy, look. I
love Sarah, you know?

03:05.875 --> 03:12.458
And um, if she found out, it
would just be a disaster.

03:12.458 --> 03:14.667
Especially with this rough
patch that we're goin' through.

03:14.667 --> 03:20.708
Yeah, no. Absolutely, I mean,
I love Brad so this ends here.

03:20.708 --> 03:22.542
Yeah.

03:24.958 --> 03:27.875
I should uh, go.

03:27.875 --> 03:28.750
Amy.

03:31.750 --> 03:33.083
We're gonna be OK.

03:33.083 --> 03:40.333
♪

03:40.333 --> 03:42.500
(door opens and closes)

03:42.500 --> 03:44.375
(exhale)

03:46.250 --> 03:47.958
I can't talk much now, honey,

03:47.958 --> 03:49.292
I have Sue here with me.

03:49.292 --> 03:51.167
I just wanted to let you
know we're on our way.

03:51.167 --> 03:52.250
-Yeah, uh.

03:54.083 --> 03:56.875
Good. Well, uh talk
when you get home.

03:56.875 --> 03:59.333
Yeah. It'll just be a few hours.

03:59.333 --> 04:00.917
I can't wait to see you, honey.

04:00.917 --> 04:04.792
Yeah. Drive safe.

04:04.792 --> 04:07.042
OK, bye!

04:07.042 --> 04:07.958
Bye.

04:20.583 --> 04:23.375
Brad! What are you doing
in the dark? You scared me.

04:23.375 --> 04:26.042
Do you have any idea how
worried I was last night?

04:26.042 --> 04:27.375
You didn't answer
any of my calls;

04:27.375 --> 04:28.792
you didn't answer my texts.

04:28.792 --> 04:31.250
I know, I was so tired,
I just fell asleep

04:31.250 --> 04:33.042
as soon as I got into the room.

04:33.042 --> 04:36.000
My phone must have
been on silent.

04:36.000 --> 04:39.583
You know, I never minded that
you didn't take my last name.

04:39.583 --> 04:43.958
But I do care about
showing you off as my wife.

04:43.958 --> 04:48.000
Well, it is Amy
Greene at work.

04:48.000 --> 04:51.875
Otherwise, it is Mrs.
Bradley Collins all the way.

04:54.000 --> 04:54.875
(kiss)

04:56.500 --> 04:57.667
Mmm.

05:00.208 --> 05:01.792
(sigh)

05:02.875 --> 05:03.792
You wanna get some pizza?

05:04.917 --> 05:07.792
Yeah! Pizza sounds good.

05:07.792 --> 05:11.625
Hey, listen um, I,
I'm sorry. I just...

05:11.625 --> 05:14.250
well, you know how I get
when you're not here;

05:14.250 --> 05:16.708
I just, I can't
get any sleep and...

05:16.708 --> 05:17.625
(phone chimes)

05:17.625 --> 05:20.833
♪

05:20.833 --> 05:22.042
Who's that?

05:22.042 --> 05:23.292
It's just work.

05:24.333 --> 05:25.542
They're texting you this late?

05:29.208 --> 05:30.625
Who's "K"?

05:30.625 --> 05:32.542
Um. K is Kathy from work.

05:34.542 --> 05:36.292
(whispers) Right.

05:37.458 --> 05:38.625
What about last night?

05:38.625 --> 05:40.708
♪

05:40.708 --> 05:43.042
You said you went to bed
right after the conference.

05:46.208 --> 05:50.292
I knew something was up when
you didn't answer my calls.

05:50.292 --> 05:52.875
So, I'm gonna ask you again.

05:52.875 --> 05:55.167
Who's K?

05:55.167 --> 05:58.833
Uh, K is a realtor
from the office.

06:00.708 --> 06:01.792
A man.

06:01.792 --> 06:04.917
♪

06:04.917 --> 06:05.875
So you were with someone?

06:11.375 --> 06:13.708
The truth, Amy!

06:13.708 --> 06:16.667
We've been married for five
years. Tell me the truth!

06:20.167 --> 06:23.292
I'm not gonna lie
to you, Brad.

06:23.292 --> 06:28.708
Kent is a friend
from the office

06:28.708 --> 06:32.333
and we've just been
talking for a while and...

06:34.375 --> 06:36.458
Yes, something happened
at the conference,

06:36.458 --> 06:40.083
but it was the only time, I
swear. And the last.

06:40.083 --> 06:44.208
And I'm so, so sorry.

06:44.208 --> 06:45.500
So you're
leaving me then.

06:45.500 --> 06:48.708
No, no, no! I l love you. I
don't love him.

06:48.708 --> 06:54.667
Well. How could you do
this to our marriage?

06:54.667 --> 06:57.542
How could you do this,
Amy? You, you broke us!

06:57.542 --> 06:58.792
Don't say that.

06:58.792 --> 07:00.125
You broke us!

07:00.125 --> 07:00.958
(screams)

07:00.958 --> 07:02.208
Amy? Amy!

07:02.208 --> 07:04.208
(tumbling)

07:04.208 --> 07:07.208
♪

07:07.208 --> 07:11.208
Amy? Amy! No, no,
no. Please no!

07:11.208 --> 07:16.167
I'm gonna call for help,
OK? I'm gonna call for...

07:16.167 --> 07:19.750
Stay with me. Stay
with me. Amy!

07:25.792 --> 07:28.583
(birdsong)

07:28.583 --> 07:30.042
Sarah: Lucy! Come
on, let's go!

07:30.042 --> 07:30.917
We're gonna be late!

07:35.083 --> 07:36.375
Morning.

07:36.375 --> 07:37.417
Morning.

07:39.708 --> 07:41.042
Thank you.

07:42.167 --> 07:42.958
Did you get home late?

07:45.125 --> 07:47.458
Yeah, uh, you were asleep, and
I didn't want to wake you

07:47.458 --> 07:51.208
so... I just slept
in the den.

07:51.208 --> 07:53.417
Did you have a
good time?

07:54.625 --> 07:56.333
The conference?
-Oh!

07:56.333 --> 07:57.625
Was it any good?

07:57.625 --> 08:00.167
Right, um... you know,
it wasn't as boring

08:00.167 --> 08:02.667
as I thought it would be.

08:02.667 --> 08:03.958
Just really happy
to be home.

08:07.292 --> 08:08.958
Lucy! Madison's
gonna be here soon!

08:11.875 --> 08:13.708
You know, now that I'm
working full time,

08:13.708 --> 08:16.042
I'm not gonna be here all the
time to get her out the door.

08:18.292 --> 08:20.917
Are you
listening to me?

08:20.917 --> 08:23.375
Sorry. I just want to see if
there's any action

08:23.375 --> 08:25.708
on that Maple
Avenue listing.

08:25.708 --> 08:28.042
I'm here. You can
stop yelling now.

08:28.042 --> 08:30.250
Happy Birthday!

08:30.250 --> 08:31.417
Happy Birthday, baby!

08:31.417 --> 08:33.458
Thank you!

08:33.458 --> 08:35.833
How was Washington, Dad?

08:35.833 --> 08:39.000
Yeah, you know, just a work
trip. No big deal.

08:39.000 --> 08:41.917
Oh, uh, Dad is going to pick you
up after cheer practice.

08:41.917 --> 08:43.417
Did you tell him
about our plan?

08:43.417 --> 08:44.583
I did not.

08:44.583 --> 08:45.833
What plan?

08:45.833 --> 08:48.292
Birthday dinner
tonight at Michael's.

08:48.292 --> 08:50.125
You don't have to
work, do you?

08:50.125 --> 08:52.292
Come on, you think I would miss
your big birthday dinner?

08:52.292 --> 08:53.375
Promise?

08:53.375 --> 08:55.792
Lucy! Who's gonna pay? Mom?

08:55.792 --> 08:56.833
Dad!

08:58.542 --> 08:59.625
(doorbell rings)

08:59.625 --> 09:01.042
Oh, you gotta go.

09:01.042 --> 09:02.125
K.

09:02.125 --> 09:03.042
Here you go!

09:03.042 --> 09:04.208
Have a good day.

09:04.208 --> 09:05.042
Love you, Mom.

09:05.042 --> 09:05.708
See you later.

09:05.708 --> 09:07.125
Bye, Dad.
-Bye, kiddo.

09:08.667 --> 09:12.917
And... I am going to go as
soon as I find my phone.

09:17.708 --> 09:22.250
♪ (haunting music)

09:22.250 --> 09:31.917
♪

09:31.917 --> 09:33.750
You're just in time to help me
decide on these curtains.

09:34.875 --> 09:37.625
All right. Let's
see what we have.

09:37.625 --> 09:41.083
Um, this one.

09:41.083 --> 09:43.292
Definitely! Great!

09:46.667 --> 09:48.750
Everything good at home?

09:48.750 --> 09:51.875
Uh, today, yes. It's
Lucy's birthday,

09:51.875 --> 09:54.125
so Kent and I are on
our best behavior.

09:54.125 --> 09:59.167
That's good. Let's go for
coffee later and talk?

09:59.167 --> 10:00.167
Sounds good.

10:07.208 --> 10:09.292
Miguel.

10:09.292 --> 10:12.542
Let's set up a meeting at 11. I
want to talk to everybody, OK?

10:12.542 --> 10:13.667
Sounds good, boss.

10:24.125 --> 10:27.292
Hey. What's goin' on?

10:27.292 --> 10:28.583
You didn't see the
company email?

10:29.292 --> 10:31.042
Email about what?

10:31.042 --> 10:33.375
(sigh) Amy Greene.

10:33.375 --> 10:35.958
What about her?

10:35.958 --> 10:38.375
An accident at home. She fell
down the stairs and...

10:40.708 --> 10:42.708
she died.

10:45.583 --> 10:47.375
Oh, my God.

10:47.375 --> 10:48.750
Yeah.

10:50.500 --> 10:51.958
(sigh)

10:53.542 --> 11:01.000
(door opens and closes)

11:01.000 --> 11:02.500
(taps head lightly on door)

11:02.500 --> 11:08.250
♪

11:11.083 --> 11:21.042
♪

11:22.458 --> 11:24.125
(sigh)

11:24.125 --> 11:34.083
♪

11:39.125 --> 11:49.083
♪

11:51.833 --> 11:53.458
Lucy's 18 now?

11:53.458 --> 11:54.625
Agh, I know.

11:54.625 --> 11:55.833
(giggle)

11:55.833 --> 11:57.375
And Madison next month?

11:57.375 --> 11:59.375
Mm hm.

11:59.375 --> 12:03.625
God, that
makes us... old!

12:03.625 --> 12:06.208
No! Ugh.

12:06.208 --> 12:09.292
But I do have something to help
with that.

12:09.292 --> 12:12.875
A girl's spa weekend, you, me
and our two babies.

12:12.875 --> 12:15.208
I love it! Madison will, too!

12:15.208 --> 12:15.875
Good.

12:15.875 --> 12:17.833
(excited exhale)

12:20.875 --> 12:24.375
So you and Kent. You guys still
working on things?

12:24.375 --> 12:29.125
We're trying. But he always
seems so distracted.

12:29.125 --> 12:32.250
And if I ask what's wrong, he
just clams up so...

12:33.708 --> 12:37.042
A marriage really changes over
the years.

12:37.042 --> 12:39.500
We change, and the kids grow up.

12:41.958 --> 12:46.333
It's true. I just hope we can
work everything out, you know?

12:46.333 --> 12:52.000
♪ (threatening music)

12:52.000 --> 13:01.958
♪

13:06.958 --> 13:16.917
♪

13:17.958 --> 13:23.292
♪ (soft bar music)

13:23.292 --> 13:24.708
Hey.

13:24.708 --> 13:26.583
Where's Lucy? I thought
you were picking her up.

13:26.583 --> 13:28.750
Practice is running late;
Madison's gonna drop her off.

13:28.750 --> 13:30.167
She'll be here any minute.

13:30.167 --> 13:31.417
OK.

13:33.792 --> 13:36.708
You know I was thinking?

13:36.708 --> 13:42.042
We um, we raised a child for 18
years.

13:42.042 --> 13:43.875
(laugh) Yeah, we did.

13:43.875 --> 13:45.333
A good child.

13:47.542 --> 13:48.833
With the best mom.

13:54.542 --> 13:59.000
I think we just... we lost track
of what we need.

13:59.000 --> 14:02.000
Not as parents, but as a couple.

14:02.000 --> 14:05.833
Yeah, I know and I blame myself
for that.

14:05.833 --> 14:08.917
I know, I get so wrapped up in
work and then I bring it home.

14:08.917 --> 14:12.208
Yeah, and that's what I mean,
Kent.

14:12.208 --> 14:15.625
You need to ask yourself if
you're happy.

14:15.625 --> 14:17.375
Should you maybe, I don't know,

14:17.375 --> 14:20.208
maybe think about another job
or...?

14:20.208 --> 14:22.750
Look for another job when I'm up
for partner? Come on.

14:22.750 --> 14:24.708
No, OK. Well, then what is it?

14:24.708 --> 14:26.625
Are you nervous about Lucy
leaving?

14:26.625 --> 14:30.208
Are you unhappy with me?

14:32.375 --> 14:34.167
No, of course I'm not.

14:34.167 --> 14:37.958
OK. Just do what you need to do
for work,

14:37.958 --> 14:40.250
but stay connected to Lucy and
me, OK?

14:43.208 --> 14:44.708
I will.

14:44.708 --> 14:46.333
OK.

14:46.333 --> 14:47.708
Hey!

14:47.708 --> 14:49.542
Hey!

14:49.542 --> 14:51.125
Sorry, here. Sit.

14:53.542 --> 14:54.750
You guys, OK?

14:54.750 --> 14:55.708
Yeah!

14:55.708 --> 14:56.792
Yeah.

14:56.792 --> 14:58.042
All good, birthday girl.

14:58.042 --> 15:00.917
Happy 18th! (excited sound)

15:00.917 --> 15:05.917
So, any words of wisdom after 18
years. Ugh.

15:05.917 --> 15:12.167
Um, let's see. "Love and be
loved"?

15:12.167 --> 15:14.667
That's pretty perfect.

15:14.667 --> 15:16.458
Yeah, can't argue with that one.

15:16.458 --> 15:21.042
I can honestly say I am so over
high school. And ready to...

15:21.042 --> 15:23.458
So ready to what?
Abandon your parents?

15:23.458 --> 15:24.667
(laughs)

15:24.667 --> 15:25.875
Leave us all alone in our house?

15:25.875 --> 15:27.583
To start college.

15:27.583 --> 15:28.708
It's the same thing, Luce.

15:28.708 --> 15:30.125
Oh, my goodness.

15:30.125 --> 15:31.542
So how was practice?

15:31.542 --> 15:34.000
I'm dead. We had another killer
session today

15:34.000 --> 15:36.042
'cause we play East Ridge next
but...

15:36.042 --> 15:39.083
thinking about this
meal got me through it.

15:39.083 --> 15:42.667
I bet I know exactly what
the birthday girl wants.

15:42.667 --> 15:43.583
Oh, before that.

15:45.875 --> 15:47.583
We got you
this.

15:55.458 --> 15:59.333
It's beautiful! (exhale)

15:59.333 --> 16:01.042
Thank you, guys!

16:01.042 --> 16:02.708
Here, honey. Let me
help you put it on.

16:02.708 --> 16:04.625
(phone dings)

16:04.625 --> 16:06.250
(clears throat)

16:06.250 --> 16:08.333
♪ (dramatic music)

16:08.333 --> 16:11.583
Dad. What is it?

16:11.583 --> 16:14.000
Kent?

16:14.000 --> 16:18.250
Oh, um. So-called
guaranteed buyer;

16:18.250 --> 16:20.083
they're pulling out of escrow.

16:20.083 --> 16:22.375
That's not good.
But can we...

16:22.375 --> 16:26.458
can we maybe hold
it off until after dinner?

16:26.458 --> 16:28.958
Dad? Hello?

16:28.958 --> 16:31.042
Do it for Lucy,
if not me, OK?

16:34.000 --> 16:37.333
OK. Sorry, guys. I'm outta here.

16:37.333 --> 16:39.542
Lucy, honey, I'm sorry.
Look, phone's down.

16:39.542 --> 16:41.542
No more distractions, OK?

16:41.542 --> 16:42.583
Whatever.

16:42.583 --> 16:43.542
Please, Luce!

16:43.542 --> 16:44.625
OK, just wait. I
will drive you.

16:47.208 --> 16:49.500
On her birthday?
Seriously?

16:51.542 --> 16:52.625
I'll meet you at home, OK?

16:52.625 --> 16:54.250
You know what?

16:54.250 --> 16:57.542
Since clearly you cannot give
our daughter what she deserves?

16:57.542 --> 16:58.583
Just don't bother.

16:58.583 --> 17:08.542
♪

17:09.792 --> 17:11.750
(door opens)

17:11.750 --> 17:13.708
Hey, I was looking for you.

17:13.708 --> 17:14.875
(door closes)

17:14.875 --> 17:17.417
Oh, yeah? Why's that?

17:17.417 --> 17:21.125
So you could admit to being a
low life for taking that photo?

17:21.125 --> 17:25.375
( chuckle ) You
messed up, not me.

17:25.375 --> 17:28.375
Sleeping with a junior
agent who reports to you?

17:28.375 --> 17:31.500
Risking a lawsuit because you
couldn't keep it in your pants?

17:31.500 --> 17:35.000
Hey. You don't know
anything about me and Amy.

17:35.000 --> 17:37.542
Yes, I do. And I think that
photo says it all.

17:37.542 --> 17:41.125
All that photo says is that
you're trying to blackmail me.

17:41.125 --> 17:43.375
Amy's dead. You never
should've involved her.

17:43.375 --> 17:47.000
And I'm not playing your game,
Miguel. The partnership's mine.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.208
You think Jackie wants
a partner who's married

17:49.208 --> 17:51.667
and is sleeping with
his employees?

17:51.667 --> 17:55.125
It's not about a partnership.
It's about a job.

17:55.125 --> 17:57.250
Good luck finding another
one in the industry

17:57.250 --> 17:59.583
when everyone realizes how you
treat your female staff.

17:59.583 --> 18:02.792
Jackie wants to find the
best realtor as a partner.

18:02.792 --> 18:05.542
And that's me. And
you know it is.

18:05.542 --> 18:08.500
Well, Amy's husband
doesn't think so.

18:08.500 --> 18:12.875
He's selling their house and his
lawyer gave me the listing.

18:12.875 --> 18:14.417
Not you.

18:15.583 --> 18:19.208
That's too bad. That
lawyer made a mistake.

18:19.208 --> 18:21.583
Cause now he has to
work with a low life.

18:21.583 --> 18:25.708
♪

18:25.708 --> 18:30.417
(car arriving)

18:37.708 --> 18:38.833
Hey.

18:38.833 --> 18:39.708
Hey.

18:39.708 --> 18:41.042
Smells good.

18:41.042 --> 18:43.625
Yeah, I've got a lasagna
in the oven and salad.

18:46.208 --> 18:48.708
Is uh, Lucy home?

18:48.708 --> 18:51.708
Uh no, she and Madison went
shopping after practice.

18:54.917 --> 18:56.375
Sarah, I have to tell you
something.

18:56.375 --> 18:57.375
Mm hm?

18:59.208 --> 19:00.375
It's important.

19:06.000 --> 19:07.125
Hey.

19:09.083 --> 19:10.167
What is it?

19:14.208 --> 19:16.125
I slept with someone at the
conference.

19:19.333 --> 19:23.708
It's one time. Never done
anything like that before.

19:23.708 --> 19:25.208
And I'm so sorry.

19:27.917 --> 19:32.750
You know, I... I knew something
was off with you.

19:32.750 --> 19:36.250
But I wasn't expecting that.

19:40.792 --> 19:42.708
Who was it?

19:42.708 --> 19:44.375
Amy Greene.

19:44.375 --> 19:47.792
From your office? Oh, wow, that
is... well, that's classy.

19:51.833 --> 19:54.833
(inhale and exhale) And Amy's
dead now, right?

19:54.833 --> 19:59.250
Some weird household accident.

19:59.250 --> 20:03.208
That's a shame. You might've had
a nice life with her.

20:03.208 --> 20:05.833
Sarah, that is not what I
wanted. I love you.

20:05.833 --> 20:08.375
(breathing) Don't touch me; I
don't to hear your excuses.

20:08.375 --> 20:09.833
I don't wanna hear your--

20:09.833 --> 20:11.917
Hey!

20:11.917 --> 20:12.917
Hey, hon.

20:16.917 --> 20:18.208
What did you buy?

20:18.208 --> 20:19.958
Uh, a nice blouse.

20:19.958 --> 20:21.083
Oh.

20:21.083 --> 20:23.125
I'll show you later.
-OK.

20:23.125 --> 20:26.375
Uh, dinner is in about 15, if
you haven't eaten already.

20:26.375 --> 20:28.833
Nope. I was waiting to eat with
you guys.

20:33.708 --> 20:34.708
Mom, are you OK?

20:36.542 --> 20:37.583
(sniffs)

20:39.875 --> 20:44.750
OK. Uh... I'll be upstairs.

20:56.208 --> 21:00.167
And everyone knows,
right? Work? Jackie?

21:00.167 --> 21:02.917
Everyone except me?

21:02.917 --> 21:08.042
No, it's just Miguel. And... he
saw us at the conference.

21:08.042 --> 21:09.000
(disgusted exhale)

21:10.875 --> 21:13.667
So, now he's saying that
he's gonna tell Jackie

21:13.667 --> 21:17.417
unless I say... I don't
wanna be partner.

21:17.417 --> 21:18.667
Well, that's ridiculous.

21:18.667 --> 21:20.292
Yeah, he is ridiculous;
you have no idea.

21:20.292 --> 21:21.792
That's what you get
when you screw up.

21:23.708 --> 21:26.250
If I were Jackie, and I
found out about this,

21:26.250 --> 21:27.625
I'd kick you out immediately.

21:30.042 --> 21:33.875
So here's what we're gonna do.
What, what you're going to do.

21:38.875 --> 21:43.708
You're gonna move out.
-Sarah, no. That's...

21:43.708 --> 21:45.292
-Yeah, let me finish!
-I don't want--

21:45.292 --> 21:47.458
No, let me finish. I'm
gonna need some...

21:47.458 --> 21:51.542
Some space. Some time to think.

21:51.542 --> 21:54.042
Something I think you
need too, so... um

21:54.042 --> 21:56.458
She's leaving for school soon.

21:56.458 --> 21:57.625
Yeah, well, you should've
thought about that

21:57.625 --> 21:59.625
before you betrayed your family.

22:03.708 --> 22:04.667
OK.

22:06.583 --> 22:09.542
I'll find a place. It'll take me
a few days but I'll find it.

22:11.542 --> 22:14.375
You're a realtor.
Shouldn't take that long.

22:29.375 --> 22:35.875
♪ (eerie music)

22:35.875 --> 22:45.833
♪

22:49.917 --> 22:51.875
(knock at door)

22:51.875 --> 22:52.875
Excuse me?

22:52.875 --> 22:55.042
Oh, hi. Can I help you?

22:55.042 --> 22:59.750
Yeah! Um, I was just walking
around your neighborhood.

22:59.750 --> 23:02.417
I recently moved in. And I'm in
desperate need of someone

23:02.417 --> 23:04.625
to help me decorate my rather...

23:04.625 --> 23:06.750
lonely, sad bachelor place.

23:06.750 --> 23:09.500
(laugh) Well, you found a
good place for that.

23:09.500 --> 23:12.375
We are definitely known for
cheering up sad homes.

23:12.375 --> 23:14.458
Fantastic! My
lucky day. I'm Brad.

23:14.458 --> 23:16.375
Hi, I'm Sarah.
Nice to meet you.

23:16.375 --> 23:17.375
Nice to meet you.

23:18.458 --> 23:21.375
This is um, this is
quite the shop.

23:21.375 --> 23:24.292
Thank you! We
can do it all.

23:24.292 --> 23:25.792
What exactly
do you need?

23:25.792 --> 23:29.667
Everything. But mostly
a professional eye

23:29.667 --> 23:31.708
because I have no
idea what I'm doing.

23:31.708 --> 23:36.583
(laugh) Well, that is easy. Uh,
let me just grab my card.

23:36.583 --> 23:39.167
There you go and I can stop by
and give you some ideas,

23:39.167 --> 23:40.458
if you'd like.

23:40.458 --> 23:42.333
Well, this is gonna make
my move a lot easier.

23:42.333 --> 23:44.375
We will do our very best.
-Thank you.

23:44.375 --> 23:46.333
Hey, by the way, where
exactly are you from?

23:46.333 --> 23:49.208
Washington. The city,
not the state.

23:49.208 --> 23:50.833
Welcome.

23:50.833 --> 23:52.208
Thank you.

23:52.208 --> 23:53.417
It's a pleasure
to meet you.

23:53.417 --> 23:54.667
Pleasure meeting
you, Sarah.

24:05.958 --> 24:07.792
Sarah: He says they only
slept together once.

24:09.000 --> 24:11.458
Once is enough with
something that serious.

24:13.542 --> 24:17.292
Sarah, you're allowed
to be angry, you know.

24:17.292 --> 24:19.083
And you're allowed
to show it.

24:19.083 --> 24:23.958
I know. I am angry. But I'm more
confused than anything.

24:23.958 --> 24:26.208
I just... I don't know
where the two of us

24:26.208 --> 24:27.792
are supposed go from here.

24:27.792 --> 24:31.417
Don't go anywhere or do
anything till you're ready.

24:31.417 --> 24:33.208
Take your time now.

24:33.208 --> 24:35.125
I will. I will. Just...

24:35.125 --> 24:37.208
(big sigh)

24:37.208 --> 24:39.917
Though I did tell Kent he had
to move out for a while.

24:39.917 --> 24:43.958
Really? Well, that should
get his attention.

24:43.958 --> 24:45.500
Right?

24:45.500 --> 24:47.458
Look, if you need
some time off.

24:47.458 --> 24:50.500
No, no, I... thank
you, but no.

24:50.500 --> 24:52.333
I just want to keep
working so this doesn't

24:52.333 --> 24:55.875
totally overwhelm
me or something.

24:55.875 --> 24:58.708
OK, (her phone chimes) but
if you change your mind.

24:59.375 --> 25:03.042
Shoot.

25:03.042 --> 25:07.000
I'm late for my meeting. I
gotta run. See you in a bit?

25:07.000 --> 25:11.625
Yeah. Sure thing. Hey, and
thank you for the offer.

25:11.625 --> 25:13.167
Of course.
See ya later.

25:13.167 --> 25:15.417
OK.

25:15.417 --> 25:23.917
♪ (brooding music)

25:23.917 --> 25:33.875
♪

25:38.333 --> 25:41.208
(phone rings)

25:41.208 --> 25:43.083
Hey! I was just
about to call you.

25:43.083 --> 25:44.375
Oh, yeah?

25:44.375 --> 25:46.542
Yeah. I found a place,
near Main and 3rd.

25:46.542 --> 25:49.833
It's... it's boring
but it's furnished.

25:49.833 --> 25:51.792
I'm getting stuff out
of the house now.

25:51.792 --> 25:53.167
I'll be outta here tonight.

25:53.167 --> 25:55.417
Good. You and Lucy should
go to dinner tonight

25:55.417 --> 25:57.708
so you can explain to
her what's going on.

25:57.708 --> 25:59.042
Sarah, do you think--

25:59.042 --> 26:01.208
I was calling because I
just found a souvenir

26:01.208 --> 26:02.542
of you and Amy.

26:02.542 --> 26:03.708
What?

26:03.708 --> 26:05.708
A photo of you and
Amy on my car.

26:07.333 --> 26:09.167
I can't believe that guy.

26:09.167 --> 26:10.583
I presume you mean Miguel.

26:10.583 --> 26:12.292
Yes, Miguel. Who the
hell else would do it?

26:12.292 --> 26:13.625
(scoff) That depends!

26:13.625 --> 26:15.750
How many people saw you
and Amy fooling around?

26:15.750 --> 26:18.542
No, Sarah, it was him.
He admitted it to me.

26:18.542 --> 26:20.208
(scoff) Does it even matter?

26:20.208 --> 26:21.833
This isn't about your
feud with Miguel.

26:21.833 --> 26:24.292
This is about you
betraying your family.

26:24.292 --> 26:26.125
Getting fired would just be
icing on the cake!

26:26.125 --> 26:33.375
♪

26:33.375 --> 26:34.292
(car door slams)

26:48.875 --> 26:50.958
Let me guess. You're
a real estate agent?

26:50.958 --> 26:52.958
You're looking
to list my home?

26:52.958 --> 26:58.000
No. What I want is for you
to leave my family alone.

26:58.000 --> 26:59.833
That photo was just
a friendly reminder.

26:59.833 --> 27:01.708
Well, here's my
friendly reminder.

27:01.708 --> 27:04.333
Don't you ever mess
with my wife again.

27:04.333 --> 27:05.708
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

27:05.708 --> 27:07.542
You do realize that
my security camera's

27:07.542 --> 27:09.250
facing the
driveway, right?

27:09.250 --> 27:11.583
Why don't you give a little
smile and wave to HR?

27:17.250 --> 27:20.375
Hey, Kent! Drive safe.

27:20.375 --> 27:26.125
(door opens and closes)

27:29.875 --> 27:32.750
Yeah. I'll talk to you
soon, Carly. OK, bye.

27:36.500 --> 27:37.875
Hey.

27:37.875 --> 27:38.750
Hey.

27:40.667 --> 27:43.208
Um, Lucy is on
her way home.

27:43.208 --> 27:44.750
I told her that you
two are having dinner

27:47.000 --> 27:49.625
I'm not looking forward
to that conversation.

27:50.792 --> 27:52.167
Yeah, I believe you.

27:54.208 --> 27:58.167
(door opens and closes)

27:59.792 --> 28:01.375
Hey, honey.

28:01.375 --> 28:03.708
We still going for dinner?

28:03.708 --> 28:05.625
Yeah, we'll leave whenever
you're ready, OK?

28:07.583 --> 28:11.083
OK. Uh, just give me five
minutes to change.

28:11.083 --> 28:12.333
OK. No rush.

28:18.625 --> 28:22.375
Sarah. I'm gonna miss
seeing her every day.

28:25.875 --> 28:28.333
Kent, I will be honest.
I need this time apart.

28:31.708 --> 28:33.333
But I would never keep
your daughter from you.

28:40.375 --> 28:42.125
(phone rings)

28:45.208 --> 28:46.500
Hey.

28:46.500 --> 28:48.625
Hey Lu, how's it going?

28:48.625 --> 28:51.708
Well, something's going
on with my mom and dad.

28:51.708 --> 28:53.500
You mean like another fight?

28:53.500 --> 28:59.667
Yeah, well, worse, actually.
My dad's moving out.

28:59.667 --> 29:01.125
What?

29:01.125 --> 29:04.667
He's taking me for dinner.
Without my mom. So...

29:04.667 --> 29:06.875
Believe me. You do not want
to have this conversation

29:06.875 --> 29:08.208
in a public place.

29:08.208 --> 29:11.625
Yeah? Um, yeah, I'll
tell him I want to have

29:11.625 --> 29:13.958
our talk at home before we go.

29:17.500 --> 29:27.458
♪ (eerie music)

29:30.375 --> 29:32.208
Lucy: So did you love
this woman or what?

29:32.208 --> 29:33.417
No, Lucy, honey...

29:37.042 --> 29:38.375
Obviously, we were close.

29:38.375 --> 29:39.750
(chortles) Obviously.

29:42.042 --> 29:47.375
Lucy, honey, I am so
sorry for this mess.

29:47.375 --> 29:49.083
You have no idea how
much I love you guys.

29:52.917 --> 29:54.958
(inhale) I know you love us.

29:58.958 --> 30:01.292
I just never thought you'd
do something like this.

30:05.833 --> 30:08.000
Me either, sweetheart.

30:08.000 --> 30:09.917
-I'm really gonna miss
having you at home.

30:12.125 --> 30:16.250
Well, three months, you're
gonna be off hanging out

30:16.250 --> 30:18.083
with all your new
college friends.

30:18.083 --> 30:19.667
There's no time
to miss your dad.

30:19.667 --> 30:20.625
(tearful laughter)

30:20.625 --> 30:23.125
No. No way!

30:23.125 --> 30:26.708
You are still taking me to the
campus tour on the 27th.

30:26.708 --> 30:28.375
Campus tour on
the 27th...

30:28.375 --> 30:31.542
the one you reminded
me about 575 times?

30:31.542 --> 30:33.000
Yeah, I think
I'll remember.

30:33.000 --> 30:36.542
♪

30:36.542 --> 30:38.042
Let's go get
some food, huh?

30:38.042 --> 30:39.333
Yeah.

30:44.792 --> 30:45.792
I love you.

30:52.250 --> 30:53.250
(birdsong)

30:53.250 --> 30:54.792
Sarah: Hey, honey.
Lucy: -Hey.

30:54.792 --> 30:56.167
Did you have a
good day today?

30:57.000 --> 31:00.208
Um... no, actually,
I've had better.

31:02.292 --> 31:03.083
Mom?

31:03.083 --> 31:04.917
Yeah?

31:04.917 --> 31:10.167
I was thinking. Would a
therapist or counsellor

31:10.167 --> 31:12.917
or something, help you
and Dad work stuff out?

31:12.917 --> 31:15.708
Oh, honey, I hear
you on this.

31:15.708 --> 31:17.208
But?

31:17.208 --> 31:20.250
Could it help?
Honestly, yes.

31:20.250 --> 31:21.500
But I'm just not ready
to go there yet.

31:23.500 --> 31:25.833
You mean, you're not ready to
forgive Dad for cheating.

31:28.917 --> 31:32.458
Which I can
understand, Mom.

31:32.458 --> 31:36.708
Thank you. You know, that's
the thing about emotions;

31:36.708 --> 31:39.208
they're not on
any schedule.

31:39.208 --> 31:44.375
Yeah, I know. It's just...
It's just so depressing.

31:44.375 --> 31:48.042
I'm so sorry we put you
in this situation, Luce.

31:48.042 --> 31:51.500
I'm sure we can find a
way through this, OK?

31:51.500 --> 31:54.667
Yeah. I really
hope so.

31:54.667 --> 31:57.625
I know, honey.
(exhale) I know.

31:57.625 --> 32:02.000
♪

32:02.000 --> 32:04.375
(phone beeps)

32:04.375 --> 32:05.625
Sarah: Hello?

32:05.625 --> 32:07.375
Hi, Sarah. It's Brad.

32:07.375 --> 32:08.875
Oh, yeah, hi.

32:08.875 --> 32:10.083
Hope I'm not calling
you too late.

32:10.083 --> 32:12.250
(laugh) No, not at all.

32:12.250 --> 32:14.667
I was just phoning to see
if we could set up a time

32:14.667 --> 32:16.458
for you to come see my place.

32:16.458 --> 32:19.500
Sure! Let me just
check my calendar.

32:19.500 --> 32:23.708
-Um, you know what? I have a
break in my schedule tomorrow.

32:23.708 --> 32:25.542
Would that work for you?

32:25.542 --> 32:29.000
Uh, tomorrow. I think
so. Yeah, what time?

32:29.000 --> 32:30.875
11 am? Or whatever
works best for you.

32:30.875 --> 32:32.667
Yeah, 11 works.

32:32.667 --> 32:34.667
And if you just wanna send me
your address, that'd be great.

32:34.667 --> 32:36.125
Great. I'll see you then.

32:38.792 --> 32:39.625
Lucy: Who was that?

32:39.625 --> 32:41.333
Just a new client.

32:41.333 --> 32:42.750
All right.

32:42.750 --> 32:44.875
Let's watch a movie.

32:44.875 --> 32:46.958
But not some old boring
black-and-white thing.

32:46.958 --> 32:49.292
Oh, listen to you,
Miss Bossy Pants.

32:49.292 --> 32:51.583
Hello, I made the
popcorn, so I choose.

32:51.583 --> 32:53.542
OK, well then I'm gonna
hold the popcorn.

32:53.542 --> 32:54.458
All right.

32:54.458 --> 32:55.250
(chuckles)

33:00.250 --> 33:02.292
Brad: So, what do you think?

33:03.667 --> 33:08.750
Uh, well. There is a furniture
store next door to my office.

33:08.750 --> 33:11.500
They have some stools that
would look amazing here.

33:11.500 --> 33:13.458
And you should add some
accessories with

33:13.458 --> 33:16.042
the right color and texture
just to complete the look.

33:16.042 --> 33:17.458
Sounds great.

33:17.458 --> 33:19.667
The office will need some
additional shelving

33:19.667 --> 33:22.167
and as for the primary
bedroom, it just needs,

33:22.167 --> 33:24.458
you know, a little bit
of your personality.

33:24.458 --> 33:25.500
(chuckles)

33:25.500 --> 33:28.250
Don't worry; I'll
email you some ideas.

33:28.250 --> 33:30.542
(exhale) That would
be very helpful.

33:30.542 --> 33:34.000
Um, my wife used to handle
all the decorating.

33:34.000 --> 33:35.917
Oh, are you
recently divorced?

33:35.917 --> 33:42.708
No. Widower, which sounds
weird to say, but um,

33:42.708 --> 33:45.333
that's why I moved.
The memories.

33:45.333 --> 33:47.833
I'm so sorry. I
didn't realize.

33:47.833 --> 33:51.000
Ah, just uh... one day
at a time, right?

33:52.792 --> 33:55.042
I can't imagine.

33:55.042 --> 33:57.042
And she must've been young,
obviously, your wife?

33:57.042 --> 33:59.583
Yeah. Too young to
die, that's for sure.

33:59.583 --> 34:01.208
Yeah.

34:01.208 --> 34:04.500
And uh, how bout
you? Married? Kids?

34:04.500 --> 34:07.833
Uh (chuckle) separated.
Pretty recently, actually.

34:07.833 --> 34:09.208
Now I'm sorry.

34:09.208 --> 34:12.958
No, it's uh, fine.
(phone rings) Excuse me.

34:12.958 --> 34:15.250
And speak of the
devil. Just one sec.

34:15.250 --> 34:15.792
Please.

34:15.792 --> 34:16.917
Thanks.

34:16.917 --> 34:18.167
Hello.

34:19.708 --> 34:21.708
Ah, yes, she's gonna stay
at your place tonight

34:21.708 --> 34:23.708
so you two can just leave
from there in the morning?

34:23.708 --> 34:26.375
♪ (dramatic music) ♪

34:26.375 --> 34:28.167
Good. So, tell them
to bid over asking.

34:30.083 --> 34:32.292
Sounds great. Uh, look,
I gotta let you go;

34:32.292 --> 34:34.417
I'm just in the middle
of something. OK.

34:36.333 --> 34:39.708
I am so sorry. I don't
normally take personal calls,

34:39.708 --> 34:42.958
but he's taking our daughter
on a college campus tour.

34:42.958 --> 34:44.083
(chuckle)

34:44.083 --> 34:46.042
I totally understand.

34:46.042 --> 34:49.292
My wife and I didn't have
kids but uh, I get it.

34:49.292 --> 34:53.208
I couldn't help overhearing uh,
you're selling your house?

34:53.208 --> 34:55.083
Oh, no no no, no.
Kent's a realtor.

34:55.083 --> 34:57.250
He's showing a house
later this week.

34:57.250 --> 34:59.458
Really not that interesting.

34:59.458 --> 35:03.208
No, it is. Ah! I mean
you're interesting.

35:07.542 --> 35:10.375
Um, so like I said,
I'll send you some

35:10.375 --> 35:12.375
design options by,
say, Friday?

35:12.375 --> 35:13.458
Yeah, that would be great!

35:13.458 --> 35:14.417
OK!

35:14.417 --> 35:16.042
I uh, I just have
one more question.

35:16.042 --> 35:17.958
Oh, yeah. Sure.

35:17.958 --> 35:22.500
Would it be weird, uh, would it
cross the client-decorator

35:22.500 --> 35:25.208
boundary if I asked
you out for a drink?

35:26.708 --> 35:29.292
Oh, uh, I, uh (laugh)

35:29.292 --> 35:31.208
No, hey, hey.
Look. I'm sorry.

35:31.208 --> 35:32.708
I didn't mean put
you on the spot.

35:32.708 --> 35:34.250
No, it's just I'm...

35:34.250 --> 35:38.875
No, no. It's OK. I imagine
that's quite hard for you too.

35:38.875 --> 35:40.667
(phone chimes)

35:40.667 --> 35:42.708
Excuse me,

35:42.708 --> 35:46.250
and I'm late for my next
appointment. (nervous giggle)

35:46.250 --> 35:47.708
I have to get running.

35:47.708 --> 35:50.875
I will get out of your
hair. Uh, thank you.

35:50.875 --> 35:52.042
No! Thank you.

35:52.042 --> 35:53.375
Just gonna grab my coat.

35:53.375 --> 35:54.958
So... we'll
talk soon?

35:54.958 --> 35:56.792
Yeah, sounds
good. Um...

35:56.792 --> 35:59.458
♪

35:59.458 --> 36:03.708
You know uh, I think we
could, we could definitely

36:03.708 --> 36:08.042
do it over a drink. Yeah. I
think that would be OK.

36:08.042 --> 36:09.750
I'd love that.

36:09.750 --> 36:12.958
♪ (pensive music)

36:12.958 --> 36:22.917
♪

36:27.958 --> 36:33.125
♪

36:33.125 --> 36:40.167
(picking sounds)

36:40.167 --> 36:42.542
(door creaks)

36:42.542 --> 36:52.500
♪

36:57.542 --> 37:07.500
♪

37:12.542 --> 37:17.625
♪

37:17.625 --> 37:27.583
♪

37:30.208 --> 37:35.458
(hissing spray)

37:37.292 --> 37:39.250
Lucy: Mom! We're leaving
for Dad's place.

37:39.250 --> 37:39.875
Sarah: I'm coming.

37:48.542 --> 37:49.792
Wow. You...

37:49.792 --> 37:51.750
look beautiful.

37:51.750 --> 37:53.542
Thanks.

37:53.542 --> 37:55.375
You having drinks
with Carly tonight?

37:55.375 --> 37:58.167
Uh, no, just
a client.

37:58.167 --> 38:02.208
Ah. OK. Well, we
should get going.

38:02.208 --> 38:03.500
Mm hm.

38:03.500 --> 38:05.125
-We'll call you
from campus.

38:05.125 --> 38:06.875
OK. Send me pictures.

38:06.875 --> 38:08.042
I will!

38:08.042 --> 38:09.125
Mmm, I hear it's
beautiful there.

38:09.125 --> 38:10.250
-Yeah, it's gonna be good.

38:11.417 --> 38:13.042
Joe's handling the
open house for me

38:13.042 --> 38:14.542
so there'll be no
distractions.

38:14.542 --> 38:16.250
Good.

38:16.250 --> 38:18.542
All right. (laugh)

38:18.542 --> 38:19.708
All right. Well,
you guys have fun.

38:19.708 --> 38:21.375
I have to finish
getting ready. OK?

38:21.375 --> 38:22.125
Bye, Mom.

38:22.125 --> 38:22.917
Bye.

38:22.917 --> 38:32.875
♪

38:35.417 --> 38:36.333
Cheers.
Cheers.

38:41.458 --> 38:43.958
I wanna thank you
for coming out.

38:43.958 --> 38:48.042
It's been... kind of lonely for
me since I moved here.

38:48.042 --> 38:49.667
Hard to meet new people?

38:49.667 --> 38:52.458
My wife and I, we weren't
really very social.

38:52.458 --> 38:55.542
Just homebodies,
I guess.

38:55.542 --> 38:59.375
Yeah, that can happen. Kent and
I were stuck in a routine.

38:59.375 --> 39:02.708
So I'm glad for this time
to figure out who I am again.

39:04.375 --> 39:06.375
And who is that?

39:06.375 --> 39:10.875
I mean, what do you
like outside of work?

39:10.875 --> 39:16.792
I like music. Opera, actually.
But Kent wasn't a real big fan.

39:16.792 --> 39:20.625
Oh, well, I'll tell you a
story. When I was a kid

39:20.625 --> 39:23.708
I saw this production
of "Aida" at the Met.

39:23.708 --> 39:26.375
There must've been a hundred
extras on the stage.

39:26.375 --> 39:27.375
and an elephant.

39:27.375 --> 39:29.083
(laughs)

39:29.083 --> 39:33.042
And I've been a fan ever since.
Of opera and elephants.

39:33.042 --> 39:34.875
(louder laugh)

39:34.875 --> 39:38.208
Opera in Philadelphia
is more scaled down.

39:38.208 --> 39:40.000
But Verdi works
everywhere.

39:40.000 --> 39:42.375
Si , naturalmente .

39:42.375 --> 39:44.375
Oh, man. I gotta
work on my Italian.

39:44.375 --> 39:45.958
(chuckle)

39:45.958 --> 39:50.542
But, if I could sing, I never
would've been a lawyer.

39:50.542 --> 39:52.375
What kind of law
do you practice?

39:52.375 --> 39:53.833
The boring kind,
unfortunately.

39:53.833 --> 39:55.000
(laugh)

39:55.000 --> 39:57.000
So uh, let's just keep
talking about you.

40:05.042 --> 40:07.750
Thank you.
That was fun.

40:07.750 --> 40:11.792
Well, you're welcome!
That makes me happy.

40:11.792 --> 40:14.042
Maybe we could do
this again sometime?

40:14.042 --> 40:15.375
Sure.

40:17.500 --> 40:19.708
Next one, I'm
thinking opera.

40:19.708 --> 40:22.167
OK.

40:22.167 --> 40:23.208
♪

40:23.208 --> 40:24.333
(soft kiss)

40:24.333 --> 40:26.000
Drive safe.

40:26.000 --> 40:26.583
Good night.

40:28.333 --> 40:29.500
Thanks!

40:29.500 --> 40:30.792
Goodnight, Sarah.

40:32.292 --> 40:35.792
(car door closes)

40:40.000 --> 40:41.208
♪

40:41.375 --> 40:44.000
Kent: You know...
I'm pretty jealous.

40:44.000 --> 40:45.542
I wish I was goin'
away to college.

40:45.542 --> 40:48.375
(laugh) Yeah, I've
heard the stories, Dad.

40:48.375 --> 40:51.500
Well, the tour
starts in two hours,

40:51.500 --> 40:53.583
and we've got a long
drive ahead of us,

40:53.583 --> 40:54.917
so... we should
hit the road.

40:54.917 --> 40:55.750
Let's do it!

40:55.750 --> 40:56.375
All right.

40:56.375 --> 40:57.375
(phone rings)

40:57.375 --> 40:58.167
Oh, one sec.

40:59.500 --> 41:01.333
Hey, Joe.

41:01.333 --> 41:03.333
Kent, I got here early to
set up for the open house,

41:03.333 --> 41:05.042
but we've got
problems.

41:05.042 --> 41:06.625
What kind of
problems?

41:06.625 --> 41:08.208
-The thermostat is broken;
I can't turn it off.

41:08.208 --> 41:09.583
It's about 90
degrees in the house

41:09.583 --> 41:10.708
and it's only getting hotter.

41:12.417 --> 41:13.958
Well, everything was
working yesterday.

41:13.958 --> 41:16.042
-And there's this
really bad smell

41:16.042 --> 41:18.333
I mean, I opened all the
windows but somehow...

41:18.333 --> 41:19.667
Just please tell me
it's gonna be fixed

41:19.667 --> 41:20.792
by the time the
Grahams come.

41:20.792 --> 41:22.417
I doubt it.

41:22.417 --> 41:23.792
(frustrated sigh)

41:23.792 --> 41:25.292
Doesn't make any sense to me!

41:25.292 --> 41:26.667
-Listen. Hey...

41:26.667 --> 41:30.708
Kent. I need you
to get here now.

41:30.708 --> 41:32.750
Joe, I've got this
thing with Lucy today.

41:32.750 --> 41:34.458
We're about to hit the road.

41:34.458 --> 41:36.000
-The Grahams are
your clients, Kent.

41:36.000 --> 41:38.000
I can't stay here all day
and just monitor things.

41:38.000 --> 41:39.958
♪

41:39.958 --> 41:41.875
OK. I'll get over
there as fast as I can

41:41.875 --> 41:44.625
and take care of
it. OK, bye.

41:44.625 --> 41:46.000
Seriously, Dad?

41:47.667 --> 41:49.625
Honey, I have to salvage
this open house.

41:49.625 --> 41:52.208
Try salvaging your
family for once!

41:52.208 --> 41:54.167
Lucy, honey, we're going to get
you to that campus tour;

41:54.167 --> 41:55.208
I promise you.

41:55.208 --> 41:56.583
Whatever.

41:57.375 --> 41:58.458
Lucy!

42:00.375 --> 42:04.833
Carly: So he's a good-looking,
opera-loving, lonely widower.

42:04.833 --> 42:09.042
Sarah: Pretty much. And
smart. And nice. (laugh)

42:09.042 --> 42:12.375
Anyway, uh, I did most
the talking. Shocker.

42:12.375 --> 42:13.708
Oh, yeah?

42:13.708 --> 42:15.583
-Yeah, he asked about
Lucy and college.

42:15.583 --> 42:17.000
He and his wife
never had kids so...

42:18.542 --> 42:20.708
How did the wife die exactly?

42:20.708 --> 42:22.250
I do not know the details.

42:23.500 --> 42:25.458
How did you two
leave things then?

42:25.458 --> 42:27.167
Oh, hey Carly, Kent's
just on the other line.

42:27.167 --> 42:29.000
I'll see you in the
office in a bit, OK?

42:29.000 --> 42:30.042
(beep)

42:30.042 --> 42:31.875
Hey, Kent, you guys
on the road?

42:31.875 --> 42:33.583
Uh, that's actually
why I'm calling.

42:33.583 --> 42:35.458
Please do not tell me.

42:35.458 --> 42:36.833
There's just something
really strange happening

42:36.833 --> 42:38.708
at that open house
and Joe needs me

42:38.708 --> 42:39.958
to get over there
right away.

42:39.958 --> 42:41.708
And of course, that
takes priority

42:41.708 --> 42:43.500
over your daughter's needs.

42:43.500 --> 42:45.458
Sarah, they're very
important clients.

42:45.458 --> 42:47.542
-They're all super
important clients.

42:47.542 --> 42:50.000
And uh, and you know?
Everything always seems

42:50.000 --> 42:52.708
to have to be done right
away for Jackie.

42:52.708 --> 42:54.500
And if your family gets
thrown under the bus,

42:54.500 --> 42:56.875
well, at least maybe you
sold a house, right?

42:56.875 --> 43:00.833
I'm sorry. I know I screwed up
with you, and now with Lucy.

43:00.833 --> 43:02.083
-OK, just stop. Just...

43:04.875 --> 43:06.375
I will...

43:06.375 --> 43:08.875
I'll cancel my morning meeting
and I'll take her myself.

43:08.875 --> 43:11.042
You and I will deal
with this later. - Thank you.

43:11.042 --> 43:13.375
Yeah, well you're gonna have
to drive Lucy over here.

43:13.375 --> 43:15.667
Yeah, of course.
We're on our way.

43:16.042 --> 43:17.042
(zipper closes)

43:21.292 --> 43:24.875
(keys clicking)

43:24.875 --> 43:34.833
♪

43:34.958 --> 43:37.208
(ringtone)

43:37.208 --> 43:38.708
Sarah: Hey.

43:38.708 --> 43:40.583
Hey! How was the tour?

43:40.583 --> 43:41.708
Oh, so now you care?

43:44.083 --> 43:47.333
We had a really good day
and Lucy loved the place

43:47.333 --> 43:49.208
She's in a much better mood now.

43:49.208 --> 43:50.875
Well, I'm glad to hear that.

43:50.875 --> 43:53.542
I tried to call her, but she's
not answering. Is she with you?

43:53.542 --> 43:55.208
No. I dropped her
off at Madison's.

43:57.208 --> 43:59.833
Well, I'm glad you had
a better day than me.

43:59.833 --> 44:01.792
I'm just back at the
Grahams' now to lock up.

44:01.792 --> 44:03.167
The repairman just left.

44:03.292 --> 44:06.792
Just stop! I don't want
to hear about that house!

44:06.792 --> 44:09.292
Or Miguel or your job.

44:09.292 --> 44:11.708
I care about Lucy, who
was hurt and angry

44:11.708 --> 44:12.875
because you let
her down again.

44:14.875 --> 44:17.750
It was an emergency, and I'm
gonna make it up to her.

44:17.750 --> 44:19.542
I promise.

44:19.542 --> 44:22.042
I don't want you to promise me;
I want you to promise her.

44:22.042 --> 44:25.042
Show her that being a father
is really important to you.

44:25.042 --> 44:27.708
Sarah, it is. And so
is being a husband.

44:27.708 --> 44:30.375
(derisive exhale)
Goodbye.

44:31.375 --> 44:32.167
Bye.

44:47.708 --> 44:51.875
♪ (bar music)

44:51.875 --> 44:53.167
Hey, can I get another?

44:59.542 --> 45:01.542
You look like you've had a day.

45:01.542 --> 45:04.125
(exhale)

45:04.125 --> 45:05.667
Really bad, huh?

45:07.125 --> 45:08.167
Thank you.

45:08.167 --> 45:11.667
Um, I don't wanna be
rude; I'm just...

45:11.667 --> 45:13.292
I'm just trying
to have a drink.

45:13.292 --> 45:16.125
So let's drink. Two tequila
shots, right here.

45:18.542 --> 45:19.750
I've had a bad day too.

45:34.625 --> 45:37.417
Poor baby. Not thirsty?

45:37.417 --> 45:44.750
♪

45:44.750 --> 45:47.708
(camera clicking)

45:47.708 --> 45:49.208
(grunts)

45:49.208 --> 45:50.833
What the hell do you
think you're doing?

45:54.000 --> 45:56.000
Thanks.

45:56.000 --> 45:57.375
It was nice to meet you.

46:00.167 --> 46:02.042
Thanks for stopping
by tonight.

46:02.042 --> 46:02.708
Well.

46:02.708 --> 46:03.875
It was a nice surprise.

46:03.875 --> 46:05.333
Thank you, for the company.

46:05.333 --> 46:15.292
♪

46:20.292 --> 46:20.792
♪

46:20.792 --> 46:21.708
Lucy! I uh...

46:21.708 --> 46:23.375
(clears throat)

46:23.375 --> 46:26.750
I thought you were staying at
Madison's a little bit later.

46:26.750 --> 46:28.958
Um, I texted you I
was coming home.

46:28.958 --> 46:31.292
but I guess you
were... busy.

46:33.625 --> 46:36.417
Um, this is my
daughter Lucy.

46:36.417 --> 46:38.375
Hi, Lucy. Bradley Collins.
It's nice to meet you.

46:38.375 --> 46:43.125
Your mom has told me so
much about you.

46:43.125 --> 46:44.375
Hi.

46:45.875 --> 46:48.750
Well! Uh, I
should get going.

46:48.750 --> 46:50.125
Yeah, mm hm.

46:50.125 --> 46:51.875
-Sarah, thank you
for the advice.

46:51.875 --> 46:55.042
And we'll chat later about
your recommendations.

46:55.042 --> 46:59.708
And uh, Lucy. Again, so
nice to meet you and um,

46:59.708 --> 47:02.042
good luck on your
college submissions.

47:02.042 --> 47:04.000
Thanks.

47:04.000 --> 47:05.500
OK.

47:05.500 --> 47:06.125
Talk later.

47:06.125 --> 47:06.833
Mm hm.

47:10.667 --> 47:13.958
(door opens and closes)

47:13.958 --> 47:16.083
So that's the guy
from the other night?

47:16.083 --> 47:17.583
The one who's
"just a client"?

47:17.583 --> 47:21.125
Lucy. I'm not ready to discuss
this with you right now.

47:21.125 --> 47:22.417
I'm sorry.

47:22.417 --> 47:24.250
So, you're not ready
to forgive Dad,

47:24.250 --> 47:26.208
and you're not ready to
discuss this with me.

47:26.208 --> 47:27.458
But you're sure ready
to date, aren't you?

47:29.375 --> 47:31.333
You know what? I'll
stay at Dad's tonight.

47:31.333 --> 47:32.750
So you can invite
your boyfriend back.

47:32.750 --> 47:34.333
Lucy, you know that's
not what he is.

47:34.333 --> 47:37.292
No, I don't, actually, because
you don't want to discuss it!

47:45.875 --> 47:48.417
(keys clicking)

47:48.417 --> 47:49.833
(knock at door)

47:49.833 --> 47:50.875
Hey.

47:51.708 --> 47:53.042
Hi.

47:53.042 --> 47:54.458
I just got off the
phone with Mom.

47:54.458 --> 47:56.417
And she's not really happy
about the way you left

47:56.417 --> 47:58.042
and came over here.

47:58.042 --> 48:00.667
Dad, the guy was in our
house, and they were...

48:00.667 --> 48:02.333
They were what?

48:02.333 --> 48:04.500
(little grunt)

48:04.500 --> 48:09.417
Drinking wine and laughing.
Sorry, but I freaked.

48:09.417 --> 48:10.500
Yeah, I get that.

48:12.875 --> 48:14.875
Was it that same guy?

48:14.875 --> 48:18.042
Yeah, that Brad guy
from Washington.

48:18.042 --> 48:19.667
Mm.

48:19.667 --> 48:22.458
I should check him out online.

48:22.458 --> 48:26.792
I didn't hear that, but
yeah, it's good; do that.

48:26.792 --> 48:28.125
(snickers)

48:28.125 --> 48:31.417
♪

48:31.417 --> 48:33.042
Look, hun, you've just
gotta be patient

48:33.042 --> 48:35.875
while Mom and I
work stuff out, OK?

48:35.875 --> 48:39.875
And remember, I made
the mistake, right?

48:42.375 --> 48:45.542
She wants to take you
shopping tomorrow.

48:45.542 --> 48:48.125
Can you please call her
and tell her you'll go?

48:49.417 --> 48:50.250
Yes.

48:51.792 --> 48:53.042
Thank you.

49:00.958 --> 49:02.042
Call Mom.

49:02.042 --> 49:04.042
(ringing tone)

49:05.792 --> 49:07.917
Collins! That was it.

49:14.208 --> 49:15.292
Not him.

49:20.167 --> 49:24.042
That disaster at the open
house can never happen again.

49:24.042 --> 49:25.375
Absolutely
not.

49:25.375 --> 49:27.583
The homeowners
found another firm,

49:27.583 --> 49:30.458
and we lost the buyers too.

49:30.458 --> 49:33.750
Honestly? I can see
Miguel being behind that.

49:33.750 --> 49:35.542
Just to sabotage me.

49:35.542 --> 49:38.458
That's a strong
accusation.

49:38.458 --> 49:41.167
There's something else I
need to talk to you about.

49:41.167 --> 49:44.208
Your relationship
with Amy Greene?

49:44.208 --> 49:47.750
It was a mistake,
I admit that.

49:47.750 --> 49:52.375
I have never let my personal
life interfere with my work.

49:52.375 --> 49:56.125
And I am heartbroken over
what happened to Amy.

49:56.125 --> 49:59.625
But Jackie, when it comes to
this place, you know me.

49:59.625 --> 50:01.167
And you know my work.

50:01.167 --> 50:04.042
I deserve that promotion.

50:04.042 --> 50:06.417
You just gotta let
me prove it to you.

50:06.417 --> 50:11.375
OK. Well, one step you could
take is working together

50:11.375 --> 50:15.292
with Miguel, instead of
always fighting it out.

50:17.458 --> 50:20.708
OK. All right.

50:20.708 --> 50:23.667
(sighs)

50:23.667 --> 50:33.625
♪

50:38.667 --> 50:47.708
♪

50:47.708 --> 50:53.208
I'm glad you came. I know last
night was... awkward.

50:53.208 --> 50:56.083
So what does he do exactly?

50:56.083 --> 50:58.125
When he's not having
a drink with you?

50:58.125 --> 50:59.500
Brad? He's a lawyer.

51:01.625 --> 51:04.917
You're angry at Dad. Me, too.

51:04.917 --> 51:07.500
But he wants our
family back. Do you?

51:07.500 --> 51:11.792
Oh, honey, I honestly
don't know what I want.

51:11.792 --> 51:13.542
That's what this
time is for.

51:15.167 --> 51:17.708
I'm not really in the mood
for shopping right now.

51:17.708 --> 51:18.917
Luce!

51:18.917 --> 51:24.708
♪

51:24.708 --> 51:26.458
What the hell?

51:26.458 --> 51:33.167
♪

51:47.042 --> 51:47.708
(keys clicking)

51:47.708 --> 51:49.542
(door closes)

51:49.542 --> 51:58.042
(foot steps)

51:58.042 --> 51:59.667
Can't we talk about this
now that we're home?

52:02.542 --> 52:03.792
Maybe later.

52:03.792 --> 52:12.542
♪

52:12.542 --> 52:19.625
(phone rings)

52:19.625 --> 52:21.500
Hey.

52:21.500 --> 52:24.125
I just got texted some pictures
of you and some bimbo

52:24.125 --> 52:26.125
in a downtown pub, kissing!

52:26.125 --> 52:28.375
What are you talking about?

52:28.375 --> 52:30.250
I can be there soon. Let's--

52:30.250 --> 52:33.458
Don't you dare come here. I
don't wanna see your face.

52:33.458 --> 52:33.833
Sarah--

52:35.042 --> 52:36.250
Hello?

52:39.000 --> 52:41.542
So there's a bathroom and this
house was showing all three.

52:41.542 --> 52:42.625
Right.

52:42.625 --> 52:44.125
Open house. The clients
come through and--

52:44.125 --> 52:46.792
Here I am, Miguel!
You want a photo?

52:46.792 --> 52:50.542
Why? You cheating on your wife
again? You want a souvenir?

52:50.542 --> 52:52.875
Oh, guys, just leave me outta
this, OK? I don't want it.

52:52.875 --> 52:55.375
Joe, it's OK.
Finish your drink.

52:55.375 --> 52:58.417
But I would be careful
what you say to Miguel.

52:58.417 --> 53:00.167
He likes to gossip with Jackie.

53:00.167 --> 53:04.250
Gossip? No. A
photo is proof.

53:04.250 --> 53:07.625
Not when it's a setup, Miguel.
Like having some barfly

53:07.625 --> 53:10.667
grab me and kiss me in this
place? Classy move.

53:12.292 --> 53:13.583
What are you
talking about?

53:13.583 --> 53:15.250
Oh, no idea, huh?

53:15.250 --> 53:18.208
Read my lips. None! You
think I'm afraid of you?

53:18.208 --> 53:19.875
I'd say it to your
face if I did it.

53:19.875 --> 53:22.417
(bang on table)

53:22.417 --> 53:26.292
I've never ever been more
serious about anything.

53:26.292 --> 53:28.250
Now I warned you not to
mess with my wife.

53:28.250 --> 53:29.917
And I'm not gonna forget that.

53:29.917 --> 53:39.250
♪

53:39.250 --> 53:40.667
To be honest, I
don't even...

53:40.667 --> 53:42.792
I don't even see Kent with
someone like that woman

53:42.792 --> 53:46.375
in the downtown pub. I don't
know, maybe it is all Miguel.

53:46.375 --> 53:49.292
Those two are really at
each other's throats.

53:49.292 --> 53:52.542
And it is unfair to Kent if
someone's sabotaging him.

53:52.542 --> 54:01.625
♪

54:01.625 --> 54:02.833
Sarah: But I'm
not going to

54:02.833 --> 54:03.917
let his job run my life.

54:03.917 --> 54:05.208
No. It should not.

54:07.708 --> 54:08.708
(dismayed sigh)

54:08.708 --> 54:10.583
-What?

54:10.583 --> 54:12.875
The power just went out!
There must be an outage.

54:12.875 --> 54:15.208
Not here. My lights are on.

54:16.792 --> 54:20.042
Oh! Yeah, it looks like I'm the
only house in the neighborhood.

54:20.042 --> 54:22.208
Must be a fuse or
something, I guess?

54:22.208 --> 54:24.500
Could be. Maybe give
Kent a call?

54:24.500 --> 54:25.500
-Yeah.

54:25.500 --> 54:26.750
I'll talk to you later, Carly.

54:32.125 --> 54:33.417
Hi!

54:33.417 --> 54:35.292
Hey, I just finished
a legal brief,

54:35.292 --> 54:36.583
and I was wondering
what you'd say

54:36.583 --> 54:38.917
to a spur-of-the-moment visit?

54:38.917 --> 54:40.500
-Well, I would be up for it,

54:40.500 --> 54:42.750
except that I'm in the middle of
a mini-emergency right now.

54:42.750 --> 54:45.000
Oh? You and Lucy OK?

54:45.000 --> 54:46.250
Yeah, she's at a
friend's house.

54:46.250 --> 54:47.792
But I just lost power here.

54:47.792 --> 54:49.583
And it seems I'm the only
house in the neighborhood.

54:49.583 --> 54:51.375
Let me come over
and take a look.

54:51.375 --> 54:53.208
No, no. I was just about to
leave a message for Kent

54:53.208 --> 54:54.250
when you called.

54:54.250 --> 54:55.167
-No, don't do that.

54:55.167 --> 54:56.250
Give me a few
minutes, OK?

54:57.167 --> 54:58.375
Are you sure you don't mind?

55:00.333 --> 55:02.708
Not at all. I'll see you soon.

55:11.292 --> 55:13.083
Thanks for coming, Brad.

55:13.083 --> 55:15.583
I'd still be sitting in the
dark if you hadn't shown up.

55:15.583 --> 55:18.583
I'm happy that I was available.

55:18.583 --> 55:20.875
Yeah. Well, I couldn't
focus anyway.

55:20.875 --> 55:22.958
Those photos really
have me frazzled.

55:24.917 --> 55:27.958
I think he has you frazzled.

55:27.958 --> 55:31.750
And the more you talk about
it, the worse it gets.

55:31.750 --> 55:36.875
Sarah. I think you're
a fascinating woman

55:36.875 --> 55:39.708
and I want to get to
know more about you.

55:39.708 --> 55:41.167
(exhale)

55:41.167 --> 55:44.583
Like, how did you
become a fan of opera?

55:44.583 --> 55:49.958
I used to sing in school.
But uh... Yeah, I...

55:49.958 --> 55:51.500
What? Opera?

55:51.500 --> 55:53.583
No! (laugh) No, I could never.

55:53.583 --> 55:56.208
I sang in a choir
in high school.

55:56.208 --> 55:58.375
And an acapella group in
college, actually.

55:58.375 --> 55:59.250
We should do karaoke.

55:59.250 --> 56:00.042
No, no!

56:00.042 --> 56:01.042
Come on!

56:01.042 --> 56:02.375
No, it's always so silly.

56:02.375 --> 56:05.583
Silly, but fun! I would
love to hear you sing.

56:08.875 --> 56:13.167
Ah, Sarah, look, I uh, I know
you haven't been separated

56:13.167 --> 56:18.917
all that long, but uh, I want
you to know I really like you.

56:18.917 --> 56:20.708
(nose exhale laugh)

56:20.708 --> 56:23.625
I do.

56:23.625 --> 56:27.208
I like you, too, but I think
it's getting late. (chuckle)

56:27.208 --> 56:28.958
(sigh) Right.

56:33.417 --> 56:35.208
Thank you. That's for
recycling right there.

56:35.208 --> 56:36.500
OK.

56:40.708 --> 56:42.458
(sigh)

56:42.458 --> 56:45.042
Well, thank you for rescuing
me, Mr. White Knight.

56:45.042 --> 56:46.375
You are welcome, milady.

56:46.375 --> 56:47.792
(laughs)

56:47.792 --> 56:49.333
Tomorrow?

56:49.333 --> 56:50.625
We'll see.

56:51.750 --> 56:54.208
Kent's not gonna be
around, though, right?

56:54.208 --> 56:57.417
Um, no, he uh, he'll
be gone all day,

56:57.417 --> 56:59.208
shopping for things for his new
place.

56:59.208 --> 57:00.917
OK.

57:00.917 --> 57:02.917
He did ask me to go with
him, but I-I said no.

57:02.917 --> 57:05.375
I love a strong woman.

57:05.375 --> 57:06.375
(nose laugh)

57:06.375 --> 57:13.333
♪

57:13.333 --> 57:15.042
(door closes)

57:15.042 --> 57:25.000
♪

57:30.000 --> 57:36.042
♪

57:36.042 --> 57:38.167
(car starts)

57:38.167 --> 57:48.125
♪

57:53.125 --> 58:02.583
♪

58:02.583 --> 58:03.958
(car door closes)

58:16.542 --> 58:19.208
Not when it's a set-up,
Miguel, like having some

58:19.208 --> 58:23.375
barfly kiss me in this
place? Classy move.

58:23.375 --> 58:24.583
What are you talking about?

58:24.583 --> 58:26.542
Oh, no idea, huh?

58:26.542 --> 58:29.583
Read my lips. None! You
think I'm afraid of you?

58:29.583 --> 58:31.125
I'd say it to your face
if I did it.

58:33.083 --> 58:33.958
Call Lucy.

58:37.500 --> 58:40.458
(phone rings)

58:42.250 --> 58:44.292
Hey, Dad, what's up?

58:44.292 --> 58:47.875
Hey, sweetie. Um, you said you
were gonna try to find out

58:47.875 --> 58:50.875
something about that guy,
Brad Mom was seeing?

58:50.875 --> 58:54.375
Yeah. He's a lawyer in some
firm with a few offices,

58:54.375 --> 58:56.833
here and in DC.

58:56.833 --> 58:59.000
But I couldn't find a personal
address for him there.

58:59.000 --> 59:00.625
Yeah, they usually keep
that stuff private.

59:02.292 --> 59:03.708
Do you want me to keep looking?

59:05.458 --> 59:08.667
Well... nobody knows the
online world like Gen Z.

59:08.667 --> 59:11.250
But um, you know, make sure
you get your homework done.

59:11.250 --> 59:14.292
(laugh) Sure, Dad, love you.

59:14.292 --> 59:15.500
I love you too.

59:17.708 --> 59:20.417
You're checking out your mom's
new boyfriend for your dad now?

59:20.417 --> 59:23.583
Well, it was my idea first. I
don't like the guy either.

59:28.375 --> 59:38.333
♪

59:41.500 --> 59:51.458
♪

01:00:01.500 --> 01:00:11.458
♪

01:00:12.250 --> 01:00:15.833
(door slides)

01:00:18.583 --> 01:00:21.042
(door slides back)

01:00:23.542 --> 01:00:33.500
(footsteps)

01:00:34.042 --> 01:00:39.792
♪

01:00:39.792 --> 01:00:44.208
Lakeside Real Estate.
This is Miguel.

01:00:44.208 --> 01:00:47.542
Yes, Mrs. Jones, yep. I'll be
here for two more hours.

01:00:47.542 --> 01:00:49.000
All right. See you
then. Bye bye.

01:00:51.667 --> 01:00:54.833
Mr. Collins. I didn't
hear you come in.

01:00:54.833 --> 01:00:56.333
Sorry you got in the
middle of this.

01:00:57.667 --> 01:00:59.500
But you can blame it
all on Kent.

01:00:59.500 --> 01:01:01.042
No, no, no, no!

01:01:01.042 --> 01:01:05.875
(grunts)

01:01:11.667 --> 01:01:13.042
(clatter)

01:01:13.042 --> 01:01:19.958
♪

01:01:19.958 --> 01:01:21.125
Hey, Joe.

01:01:21.125 --> 01:01:23.292
Hey, I just got a weird
call from that lawyer

01:01:23.292 --> 01:01:25.375
for Amy's house.

01:01:25.375 --> 01:01:26.750
Weird, how?

01:01:26.750 --> 01:01:28.708
He says the open house
is not happening.

01:01:28.708 --> 01:01:30.417
Miguel's not answering
the door, or his phone,

01:01:30.417 --> 01:01:31.708
and the house is locked.

01:01:31.708 --> 01:01:32.875
He wants to know
what's going on.

01:01:32.875 --> 01:01:34.125
Yeah, I can't blame him.

01:01:34.125 --> 01:01:36.083
I'd like to know
what's going on, too.

01:01:36.083 --> 01:01:39.208
Well, I'm calling you 'cause
Jackie has you and Miguel

01:01:39.208 --> 01:01:40.708
working together now.

01:01:40.708 --> 01:01:42.000
It's not a problem.

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:43.667
Uh, I'm just around
the corner from there.

01:01:43.667 --> 01:01:44.750
I'm gonna pop by
and see what's up.

01:01:44.750 --> 01:01:45.625
All right.

01:01:45.625 --> 01:01:55.583
♪

01:02:00.542 --> 01:02:06.500
♪

01:02:06.500 --> 01:02:12.542
(door opens and closes)

01:02:12.542 --> 01:02:14.208
♪

01:02:14.208 --> 01:02:15.208
Miguel?

01:02:15.208 --> 01:02:20.208
♪

01:02:20.208 --> 01:02:21.417
Miguel!

01:02:21.417 --> 01:02:30.625
♪

01:02:30.625 --> 01:02:31.792
Oh, my God!

01:02:38.583 --> 01:02:40.083
911. What's your emergency

01:02:40.083 --> 01:02:42.250
Hello? My colleague,
I think he's dead!

01:02:43.333 --> 01:02:46.083
So if we keep the
double doors there,

01:02:46.083 --> 01:02:47.875
that leaves a little bit
of an opening for the,

01:02:47.875 --> 01:02:49.208
for the main door.

01:02:49.208 --> 01:02:50.000
That works.

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:51.042
Yeah.

01:02:51.042 --> 01:02:52.375
Give me the dirt
about last night!

01:02:54.625 --> 01:02:56.875
There's not much to
tell. Back to this.

01:02:56.875 --> 01:03:00.917
Come on! He rides in and
rescues you from the dark?

01:03:00.917 --> 01:03:02.708
How long before you two
turned the lights out again?

01:03:02.708 --> 01:03:05.375
(laugh) (phone
rings) Hello?

01:03:07.375 --> 01:03:09.042
Miguel's dead.

01:03:09.042 --> 01:03:10.208
Dead?

01:03:10.208 --> 01:03:11.833
I found him on the floor
of his open house.

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:14.208
Stabbed, I think.

01:03:14.208 --> 01:03:16.667
(exhale) Oh, my God.
Who would do that?

01:03:16.667 --> 01:03:20.958
I don't know. But um...
Sarah, this house?

01:03:20.958 --> 01:03:24.042
(exhale) The house?
What about it?

01:03:24.042 --> 01:03:27.208
It was Amy's. She lived here.

01:03:27.208 --> 01:03:29.583
Amy from your office? That Amy?

01:03:29.583 --> 01:03:34.375
Yeah. Um, look, I'm gonna have
to um, talk to the police,

01:03:34.375 --> 01:03:38.125
you know? They're uh, they're
just... they're here.

01:03:38.125 --> 01:03:41.500
So Sarah, I'm sorry,
could I come by later?

01:03:41.500 --> 01:03:43.375
You know? I just, I can't
get it outta my head,

01:03:43.375 --> 01:03:45.042
seeing him there and
the...and the blood?

01:03:45.042 --> 01:03:47.667
Yeah, of course.
I'll see you soon.

01:03:47.667 --> 01:03:49.042
Thanks.

01:03:57.042 --> 01:03:58.917
Kent: So they're, you
know, running tests

01:03:58.917 --> 01:04:00.542
on the knife for
fingerprints.

01:04:00.542 --> 01:04:02.708
That'll clear me, I'm sure.

01:04:02.708 --> 01:04:04.167
They don't really
think you did it?

01:04:06.083 --> 01:04:08.042
They asked me about
my relationship with him,

01:04:08.042 --> 01:04:09.833
and I told 'em that we
were having issues.

01:04:09.833 --> 01:04:11.625
I had to be honest.

01:04:11.625 --> 01:04:13.708
Why would you
tell them that?

01:04:13.708 --> 01:04:15.750
Sarah, I had to
tell 'em the truth.

01:04:15.750 --> 01:04:17.500
Jackie and Joe and
everybody at the office,

01:04:17.500 --> 01:04:18.875
they're gonna do
the same thing.

01:04:21.875 --> 01:04:23.167
I had to tell 'em
about Amy, too.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:28.083
Why was Miguel selling
her house anyway?

01:04:28.083 --> 01:04:30.417
I mean, that's a little
coincidental, don't you think?

01:04:30.417 --> 01:04:33.208
Yeah, all I know is that
Amy's husband's lawyer

01:04:33.208 --> 01:04:35.083
contacted him.
So I don't know.

01:04:37.833 --> 01:04:41.042
Oh, it's almost 6;
Lucy's gonna be home soon.

01:04:41.042 --> 01:04:42.250
Do you want to
talk to her?

01:04:44.083 --> 01:04:47.250
Maybe tomorrow?
Just... I don't know;

01:04:47.250 --> 01:04:48.625
I just gotta
clear my head.

01:04:50.583 --> 01:04:52.083
I'm just gonna head
back to my place

01:04:52.083 --> 01:04:53.625
and I'll call
you later. OK?

01:04:53.625 --> 01:04:54.583
OK.

01:04:54.583 --> 01:04:55.792
All right.

01:04:55.792 --> 01:04:59.042
Hey, Kent. Look, I
um, I'm so sorry

01:04:59.042 --> 01:05:02.042
you're going
through this.

01:05:02.042 --> 01:05:03.833
You know, you really
don't deserve it.

01:05:03.833 --> 01:05:05.208
♪

01:05:05.208 --> 01:05:07.875
Thank you.

01:05:07.875 --> 01:05:10.875
And when this mess
is behind us?

01:05:10.875 --> 01:05:12.542
I'm gonna work on being
a better husband.

01:05:23.500 --> 01:05:30.000
Bye.

01:05:34.542 --> 01:05:38.292
(keys clicking)

01:05:41.458 --> 01:05:42.667
I'm just...

01:05:42.667 --> 01:05:44.042
I'm exhausted from it all.

01:05:44.042 --> 01:05:46.542
-Yeah! I get that, I mean.

01:05:46.542 --> 01:05:51.125
it all starts with him having
the affair and ends with

01:05:51.125 --> 01:05:53.000
God knows what else he's done.

01:05:53.000 --> 01:05:56.208
Well, it doesn't end with my
husband as a murderer.

01:05:56.208 --> 01:05:58.708
I'm sorry, but you do
know the expression

01:05:58.708 --> 01:06:00.500
"the wife is the last to know"?

01:06:00.500 --> 01:06:02.208
Maybe it applies to
cheating and also--

01:06:02.208 --> 01:06:04.083
Wait a sec. Are you
seriously suggesting

01:06:04.083 --> 01:06:06.167
that Kent's a killer?

01:06:06.167 --> 01:06:08.375
No. I'm sorry. I'm just
lookin' out for you, I--

01:06:08.375 --> 01:06:10.625
Because I think I know a man
pretty well after living

01:06:10.625 --> 01:06:14.333
with him and our child for
almost 20 years.

01:06:14.333 --> 01:06:18.042
You're right, I stand
"over-ruled." But I--

01:06:18.042 --> 01:06:20.500
Hey, um, someone's
at the door.

01:06:20.500 --> 01:06:23.958
OK, well, I will see you
first thing in the morning

01:06:23.958 --> 01:06:25.750
and check out those
samples you have.

01:06:25.750 --> 01:06:26.917
OK, I'll see you then.

01:06:26.917 --> 01:06:36.875
♪

01:06:40.958 --> 01:06:42.292
(door opens)

01:06:43.792 --> 01:06:44.708
Mrs. Watts?

01:06:44.708 --> 01:06:46.500
Yes.

01:06:46.500 --> 01:06:48.333
I'm Detective Phillips.

01:06:48.333 --> 01:06:50.792
You mind if I ask you a few
questions about your husband?

01:06:50.792 --> 01:06:52.625
Of course, come on in.
-Thanks.

01:06:56.125 --> 01:06:58.333
(door closes)

01:06:58.333 --> 01:06:59.917
Mom?

01:06:59.917 --> 01:07:01.333
It's OK, honey, the
uh, the detective

01:07:01.333 --> 01:07:02.750
just has a few questions.

01:07:04.375 --> 01:07:05.958
I've already told her
about Miguel's death.

01:07:05.958 --> 01:07:08.083
So is it OK if she just
stays here with us?

01:07:08.083 --> 01:07:09.417
That's totally your call.

01:07:09.417 --> 01:07:10.667
OK, hon.

01:07:11.625 --> 01:07:14.125
So you and your
husband are separated.

01:07:14.125 --> 01:07:16.875
Yes. Uh, not for
too long, though.

01:07:16.875 --> 01:07:19.500
And what was the reason
for the separation?

01:07:19.500 --> 01:07:23.167
Pretty sure he already told you
he had an affair. And with who.

01:07:23.167 --> 01:07:28.250
-Amy Greene. I'm sorry to have
to ask you this, but um,

01:07:28.250 --> 01:07:30.042
were you aware that the
deceased and your husband

01:07:30.042 --> 01:07:33.042
were um, hostile?

01:07:33.042 --> 01:07:35.667
I'm aware Miguel was
hostile with my husband.

01:07:40.667 --> 01:07:42.375
Do either of you recognize this?

01:07:43.083 --> 01:07:44.292
Oh, my God!

01:07:44.292 --> 01:07:45.917
Is that the weapon?

01:07:45.917 --> 01:07:47.250
Yeah.

01:07:47.250 --> 01:07:48.792
I don't recognize
it; should we?

01:07:50.500 --> 01:07:52.458
Mrs. Watts, do you mind
if I take a quick peek

01:07:52.458 --> 01:07:53.792
in your kitchen?

01:07:53.792 --> 01:07:56.708
Yeah, uh... of course not.
It's right this way.

01:08:07.333 --> 01:08:09.375
Looks like one's missing.

01:08:09.375 --> 01:08:12.250
OK, (scoff) that knife
did not come from here.

01:08:12.250 --> 01:08:14.292
I, I'm sure-I'm sure it's
here somewhere. Hang on.

01:08:18.167 --> 01:08:19.667
It's probably in
the dishwasher.

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:24.708
I mean, it's a pretty
common brand, right?

01:08:24.708 --> 01:08:26.417
There must be a ton of
them in Philadelphia.

01:08:26.417 --> 01:08:28.208
Yeah, except the
one that we have

01:08:28.208 --> 01:08:30.167
has your father's
fingerprints on it.

01:08:31.083 --> 01:08:32.833
My dad wouldn't kill anybody!

01:08:32.833 --> 01:08:33.917
No, he wouldn't.

01:08:33.917 --> 01:08:39.042
♪

01:08:39.042 --> 01:08:40.583
(sigh)

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:44.125
Mrs. Watts, If you
find that knife,

01:08:44.125 --> 01:08:45.542
or remember any
other information,

01:08:45.542 --> 01:08:46.750
please give me a
call immediately.

01:08:49.333 --> 01:08:50.417
OK.

01:08:51.917 --> 01:08:56.417
(door opens and closes)

01:09:04.125 --> 01:09:05.792
Mom, what's going
to happen now?

01:09:05.792 --> 01:09:06.917
(whispers) Come here.

01:09:06.917 --> 01:09:16.875
♪

01:09:21.833 --> 01:09:22.500
♪

01:09:22.500 --> 01:09:23.667
(banging)

01:09:23.667 --> 01:09:33.625
♪

01:09:35.833 --> 01:09:37.125
(banging)

01:09:37.125 --> 01:09:39.958
Police! Open up!

01:09:39.958 --> 01:09:41.458
OK, I'm coming!

01:09:41.458 --> 01:09:47.292
♪

01:09:47.292 --> 01:09:48.500
Kent Watts?

01:09:48.500 --> 01:09:50.625
Yes, but what's goin' on?

01:09:50.625 --> 01:09:52.792
You're under arrest for
the murder of Miguel Diaz.

01:09:52.792 --> 01:09:54.667
You have the right
to remain silent.

01:09:54.667 --> 01:09:56.667
Anything you say can and
will be used against you

01:09:56.667 --> 01:09:59.708
in a court of law. You have
the right to an attorney.

01:09:59.708 --> 01:10:01.792
If you cannot afford one, one
will be appointed for you.

01:10:01.792 --> 01:10:02.917
Do you understand?

01:10:04.875 --> 01:10:06.167
Yeah.

01:10:08.458 --> 01:10:11.125
Brad: They like to arrest
them late at night.

01:10:11.125 --> 01:10:13.750
Gives them uh, the
element of surprise.

01:10:13.750 --> 01:10:16.792
Yeah, I just heard
about it this morning.

01:10:16.792 --> 01:10:20.000
You should have called me; we
could've canceled the meeting.

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:23.000
To tell you the truth, I
actually wanted your advice.

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:25.458
I've called several criminal
attorneys I found online

01:10:25.458 --> 01:10:28.917
and I'm still... yeah, still
waiting for a call back.

01:10:28.917 --> 01:10:31.125
Well, you're definitely gonna
want a criminal lawyer

01:10:31.125 --> 01:10:32.833
for the case.

01:10:32.833 --> 01:10:33.958
-Yeah, I thought so.

01:10:33.958 --> 01:10:36.250
But for now, all you need
to do is have a lawyer

01:10:36.250 --> 01:10:39.708
to sit with him and...
I could do that.

01:10:39.708 --> 01:10:43.333
Oh, my God, would you?
That would be amazing

01:10:43.333 --> 01:10:45.542
and then I can just focus
on this and then focus on

01:10:45.542 --> 01:10:47.792
trying to find a
criminal attorney later.

01:10:47.792 --> 01:10:50.500
It's the least I can do.
Text me the address;

01:10:50.500 --> 01:10:53.208
I'll go down there right
now and uh, see what's up.

01:10:53.208 --> 01:10:54.625
Oh, thank you
so much.

01:11:00.042 --> 01:11:02.083
Hey, can you hear me?

01:11:02.083 --> 01:11:05.417
Sarah: Yeah. Are you OK?

01:11:05.417 --> 01:11:09.208
Given the situation. How's Lucy?

01:11:09.208 --> 01:11:14.292
Honestly? A bit of
a mess, like me.

01:11:14.292 --> 01:11:17.375
I, uh, I took her over to
Madison's for the night.

01:11:17.375 --> 01:11:19.875
I figured that would be
easier for both of us.

01:11:19.875 --> 01:11:25.708
That's good. Listen, Sarah, I
um... I don't know

01:11:25.708 --> 01:11:27.708
how that knife could have
come from our house.

01:11:27.708 --> 01:11:33.667
Yeah, I can't either. But Kent,
I know it was not you.

01:11:33.667 --> 01:11:36.708
Thanks.

01:11:36.708 --> 01:11:39.542
Hey, look, uh, I've found a
lawyer to represent you

01:11:39.542 --> 01:11:41.875
and he's on his way
there now, actually.

01:11:41.875 --> 01:11:44.750
That's good news. Who is he?

01:11:44.750 --> 01:11:46.250
Uh, Bradley Collins.

01:11:48.042 --> 01:11:49.500
The guy that you're dating?

01:11:49.500 --> 01:11:52.125
Kent, he is just a friend.

01:11:52.125 --> 01:11:53.875
Come on, Sarah. I
don't know about this.

01:11:53.875 --> 01:11:55.458
Look, he's all we have
to represent you

01:11:55.458 --> 01:11:57.042
until I hear back from a
criminal attorney.

01:11:57.042 --> 01:11:58.667
(sigh)

01:11:58.667 --> 01:12:01.542
OK, as long as you trust him.

01:12:01.542 --> 01:12:02.917
I do.

01:12:07.708 --> 01:12:11.625
Thanks for coming through for
me... you always do.

01:12:23.208 --> 01:12:26.625
Kent Watts? Brad Collins.

01:12:26.625 --> 01:12:29.042
Yeah, you're... Sarah's friend.

01:12:29.042 --> 01:12:30.625
Yes, I am.

01:12:32.625 --> 01:12:35.292
Full disclosure, we're dating.

01:12:38.750 --> 01:12:40.792
Just had to get that
out of the way.

01:12:45.958 --> 01:12:48.583
(big sigh)

01:12:48.583 --> 01:12:55.958
Look, Kent um, Kent. Look
at me. Sarah's depressed.

01:12:55.958 --> 01:12:57.917
Yeah, of course she
is. I'm depressed.

01:12:57.917 --> 01:13:00.417
This whole thing is a
complete misunderstanding.

01:13:00.417 --> 01:13:07.250
No, no, no, no. Kent. She
is very upset. I mean,

01:13:07.250 --> 01:13:08.583
It's really been
nothing but bad news

01:13:08.583 --> 01:13:09.875
since you cheated on her.

01:13:09.875 --> 01:13:12.208
OK.

01:13:12.208 --> 01:13:13.500
You don't think I know that?

01:13:15.792 --> 01:13:18.250
But I didn't kill Miguel.
Can we talk about that?

01:13:18.250 --> 01:13:21.333
Can she be sure
about that, though?

01:13:21.333 --> 01:13:22.375
I mean, she probably
believed that you weren't

01:13:22.375 --> 01:13:23.917
a philanderer, right?

01:13:23.917 --> 01:13:26.042
I'm not a philanderer.

01:13:26.042 --> 01:13:31.417
Like I told you. One time I
slept with somebody else.

01:13:31.417 --> 01:13:34.500
Zero times did I kill anybody.

01:13:34.500 --> 01:13:38.042
I'm doing my best to
keep her positive, OK?

01:13:38.042 --> 01:13:42.667
I um, I think she might need
some help. You know?

01:13:42.667 --> 01:13:47.750
Some professional help.
A psychologist.

01:13:47.750 --> 01:13:50.792
(exhale) You have to see it
from her perspective, Kent.

01:13:50.792 --> 01:13:54.208
You cheated on her, and then
this work altercation

01:13:54.208 --> 01:13:57.625
turns into a murder
investigation and...

01:13:57.625 --> 01:14:03.000
Well, you might not be
around for Sarah and Lucy.

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:08.542
She's frazzled, man.
I mean ... she's uh...

01:14:08.542 --> 01:14:11.083
Wh-what are you saying?

01:14:11.083 --> 01:14:13.625
(exhale) I'm not a mental
health expert or anything

01:14:13.625 --> 01:14:16.042
like that but... (sniff)

01:14:16.042 --> 01:14:18.875
You know, people when
they're that depressed,

01:14:18.875 --> 01:14:23.000
they have nowhere to go, no
one to reach out to and uh,

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:25.750
well, there's this tendency
to have suicidal thoughts.

01:14:27.708 --> 01:14:31.750
OK. You gotta get
me outta here!

01:14:31.750 --> 01:14:33.500
You gotta get me
outta here right now!

01:14:33.500 --> 01:14:34.833
I'm doin' my best, Kent.

01:14:34.833 --> 01:14:37.000
♪

01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:39.042
But that might not be
for a very long time.

01:14:39.042 --> 01:14:45.208
And that's gonna be a big
shock... to Sarah. And to Lucy.

01:14:45.208 --> 01:14:48.542
We need to pray that it's not
gonna be a female judge.

01:14:48.542 --> 01:14:51.708
Because, uh, well, I mean
you cheated on your wife

01:14:51.708 --> 01:14:53.333
and it was with an employee,

01:14:53.333 --> 01:14:54.833
and the employee
was a subordinate.

01:14:54.833 --> 01:14:56.458
So that kinda
reeks of coercion.

01:14:56.458 --> 01:14:57.792
That is not
what happened!

01:14:57.792 --> 01:14:59.375
That's not at all
what happened here.

01:14:59.375 --> 01:15:00.958
And then Amy dies and...

01:15:02.708 --> 01:15:05.417
apparently you had very
little concern for her.

01:15:05.417 --> 01:15:08.250
You have no idea how
I felt about Amy.

01:15:08.250 --> 01:15:11.125
You have no idea at all.

01:15:11.125 --> 01:15:13.042
And I don't know how
she's relevant here!

01:15:13.042 --> 01:15:15.042
I think that young woman
was probably relevant

01:15:15.042 --> 01:15:16.583
to a lot of people, Kent.

01:15:19.667 --> 01:15:22.458
That's not... that's
not what I meant.

01:15:24.167 --> 01:15:27.958
A bloody knife was found in her
house with your fingerprints.

01:15:30.458 --> 01:15:35.625
I understand that. But
I didn't kill with it!

01:15:35.625 --> 01:15:40.167
Keep telling yourself that.
It's good for morale.

01:15:43.292 --> 01:15:47.083
In the meantime, I will do my
best to take care of Sarah.

01:15:49.833 --> 01:15:51.708
You can count on me, Kent.

01:15:53.500 --> 01:15:54.708
Talk soon.

01:15:54.708 --> 01:16:04.000
♪

01:16:04.000 --> 01:16:07.042
(phone rings)

01:16:07.042 --> 01:16:08.250
Hey, honey.

01:16:08.250 --> 01:16:09.750
-Hi, Mom.

01:16:09.750 --> 01:16:11.333
Any updates from Dad?

01:16:11.333 --> 01:16:14.875
-Yeah. We find out tomorrow
if he makes bail.

01:16:14.875 --> 01:16:16.958
Bradley will call us right away.

01:16:16.958 --> 01:16:19.417
Wait! Him? Why?

01:16:19.417 --> 01:16:21.708
Because he is representing Dad.

01:16:21.708 --> 01:16:23.833
(scoff) That's the
best we can do?

01:16:23.833 --> 01:16:25.875
For this first step? Yes.

01:16:25.875 --> 01:16:27.125
Great.

01:16:28.708 --> 01:16:31.667
Luce? (exhale)

01:16:33.792 --> 01:16:37.417
Weren't you checking out
that Brad guy online?

01:16:37.417 --> 01:16:38.542
How about I help you with that?

01:16:40.250 --> 01:16:41.208
Yes, please. (laugh)

01:16:43.875 --> 01:16:47.875
(car door opens and closes)

01:16:47.875 --> 01:16:53.917
♪

01:16:53.917 --> 01:16:57.167
(phone ringing)
Sarah: Hey.

01:16:57.167 --> 01:17:00.375
Hey, Sarah. Just got back from
downtown talking with Kent.

01:17:00.375 --> 01:17:01.708
Yeah, how's he doing?

01:17:01.708 --> 01:17:04.625
He's holding up.

01:17:04.625 --> 01:17:07.875
Our only challenge is
gonna be the bloody knife.

01:17:07.875 --> 01:17:09.875
He didn't do it, Brad.

01:17:09.875 --> 01:17:12.583
Sarah, I know you don't want to
think he's a murderer, but

01:17:12.583 --> 01:17:14.250
he did lie to you before
about Amy Greene.

01:17:16.167 --> 01:17:19.250
so the question we have to ask
is what else is he lying about?

01:17:19.250 --> 01:17:29.208
♪

01:17:34.208 --> 01:17:34.708
♪

01:17:34.708 --> 01:17:36.208
Look, um...

01:17:36.208 --> 01:17:38.625
I have some ideas I want
to talk to you about.

01:17:38.625 --> 01:17:40.208
Can I come by in a bit?

01:17:41.833 --> 01:17:44.833
Uh, you know? I have a bit
of a headache and I think

01:17:44.833 --> 01:17:47.333
I'm just gonna relax
and run myself a bath.

01:17:47.333 --> 01:17:48.958
-Yeah, no problem.

01:17:48.958 --> 01:17:50.250
(click)

01:17:50.250 --> 01:18:00.208
♪

01:18:05.208 --> 01:18:06.875
♪

01:18:06.875 --> 01:18:08.583
Brad: What else is he
lying about? (echoes)

01:18:08.583 --> 01:18:18.542
♪

01:18:23.583 --> 01:18:33.542
♪

01:18:37.375 --> 01:18:39.542
Lucy: Whoa, whoa, whoa! There's
a Brad Collins with the

01:18:39.542 --> 01:18:41.708
same Philadelphia address
as the Miguel murder house.

01:18:41.708 --> 01:18:43.417
Let me see.

01:18:43.417 --> 01:18:45.292
That says 323 Sunset Terrace.

01:18:45.292 --> 01:18:47.625
The cops told me and my mom
that's where Amy Greene lived.

01:18:47.625 --> 01:18:49.292
The girl your dad was--

01:18:49.292 --> 01:18:52.417
So Amy and Brad were married or
living together or whatever!

01:18:52.417 --> 01:18:53.917
Drive me over there right now!

01:18:53.917 --> 01:18:56.458
How? My mom has the
car. Call an Uber.

01:18:56.458 --> 01:18:57.958
Can you? I have to call my mom.

01:19:00.292 --> 01:19:03.042
(ringing)

01:19:03.042 --> 01:19:04.917
You've reached Sarah. Leave a
message after the tone.

01:19:04.917 --> 01:19:06.875
(sigh) Shoot! Voicemail.

01:19:06.875 --> 01:19:08.333
Mom, call me as soon
as you get this!

01:19:38.208 --> 01:19:40.208
Hang on. Hang on. OK,
so you're saying that

01:19:40.208 --> 01:19:43.000
your father's lawyer
is dating your mother

01:19:43.000 --> 01:19:47.042
just happened to have been
married to Amy Greene?

01:19:47.042 --> 01:19:49.000
The woman that your father
had an affair with?

01:19:49.000 --> 01:19:52.708
Yes! Only my mom and
dad don't know that.

01:19:52.708 --> 01:19:54.375
My mom's not answering
her phone right now,

01:19:54.375 --> 01:19:56.208
so I'm on my way home.

01:19:56.208 --> 01:19:59.250
I'm worried this Brad
guy could be dangerous.

01:19:59.250 --> 01:20:01.042
And he's been to our
house a bunch of times,

01:20:01.042 --> 01:20:03.333
so he could've
grabbed the knife.

01:20:03.333 --> 01:20:06.458
Yeah. And killed Miguel to try
and frame your father.

01:20:06.458 --> 01:20:11.042
Yeah, maybe. All I know for
sure is my dad didn't do it.

01:20:11.042 --> 01:20:13.000
-OK, I'm gonna meet you
at your mother's place.

01:20:13.000 --> 01:20:14.875
But If you see that
Brad guy outside,

01:20:14.875 --> 01:20:17.542
you make sure you
wait out for me. OK?

01:20:17.542 --> 01:20:19.125
OK. Just... hurry.

01:20:19.125 --> 01:20:29.083
♪

01:20:34.083 --> 01:20:36.667
♪

01:20:36.667 --> 01:20:38.042
(yawns)

01:20:38.042 --> 01:20:38.667
Sarah.

01:20:38.667 --> 01:20:40.375
(gasp)

01:20:40.375 --> 01:20:45.083
Brad! What are you, what
are you doing here?

01:20:45.083 --> 01:20:49.500
I'm not actually here tonight.
I parked over at the mall.

01:20:49.500 --> 01:20:53.542
And I have a ticket to a movie.
That movie's playing right now.

01:20:53.542 --> 01:20:55.125
What do you want?

01:20:55.125 --> 01:20:59.458
Well. I need you to
take your medicine.

01:20:59.458 --> 01:21:00.333
What is that?

01:21:01.667 --> 01:21:04.500
Will you accept a collect call
from the Men's Central Jail?

01:21:04.500 --> 01:21:06.042
Sure. Yes! Sure.

01:21:06.042 --> 01:21:07.875
Connection active.

01:21:07.875 --> 01:21:09.500
Dad! Are you OK?

01:21:09.500 --> 01:21:13.542
Hey, honey. I'm OK. I just...
I'm worried, you know?

01:21:13.542 --> 01:21:14.750
I don't trust this Brad guy.

01:21:14.750 --> 01:21:17.208
Yeah. I know, he
was married to Amy!

01:21:17.208 --> 01:21:19.125
I just called the
cops and told them.

01:21:19.125 --> 01:21:20.542
They're on their
way to the house.

01:21:20.542 --> 01:21:23.083
Well, how do you...?

01:21:23.083 --> 01:21:24.208
Lucy, where are you?

01:21:24.208 --> 01:21:26.167
On my way home. To get Mom.

01:21:26.167 --> 01:21:28.583
OK, then I want you to get out
of there as soon as you can.

01:21:28.583 --> 01:21:30.917
I will. I'll bring her
back to Madison's house.

01:21:30.917 --> 01:21:33.708
Yeah, good girl.
Lucy, if he's there.

01:21:33.708 --> 01:21:36.125
I know, wait for the cops.

01:21:36.125 --> 01:21:39.208
(exhale) Honey, be careful.

01:21:39.208 --> 01:21:42.208
OK. I gotta go, Dad.
Love you.

01:21:44.167 --> 01:21:46.000
I want you to die, Sarah.

01:21:47.917 --> 01:21:49.583
Like my Amy.

01:21:50.625 --> 01:21:51.875
"Your Amy"?

01:21:51.875 --> 01:21:54.417
Yeah. My Amy.

01:21:58.667 --> 01:21:59.708
No, they'll know you killed me!

01:21:59.708 --> 01:22:01.417
No, no, no, no.

01:22:01.417 --> 01:22:04.542
The phone conversation
we had earlier?

01:22:04.542 --> 01:22:07.667
That's the last proof that
anybody has that we spoke.

01:22:07.667 --> 01:22:11.083
When I told you that... Kent's
chances were pretty slim

01:22:11.083 --> 01:22:13.208
of getting out, well...

01:22:13.208 --> 01:22:16.792
You just got so depressed that
you took all of these pills.

01:22:16.792 --> 01:22:18.042
No!

01:22:18.042 --> 01:22:19.125
Yeah, you did, Sarah. You did.

01:22:19.125 --> 01:22:20.208
No, please, Brad.

01:22:20.208 --> 01:22:24.500
KENT NEEDS TO FEEL WHAT I FEEL!

01:22:24.500 --> 01:22:34.458
♪

01:22:35.250 --> 01:22:39.708
Kent slept with her.
You killed her!

01:22:39.708 --> 01:22:42.458
I would never hurt my wife!

01:22:46.792 --> 01:22:48.833
I would never have hurt Amy.

01:22:48.833 --> 01:22:50.542
(breathing)

01:22:50.542 --> 01:22:52.208
(door opens)

01:22:52.208 --> 01:22:53.042
Mom?

01:22:53.042 --> 01:22:55.083
Lucy! Call the cops!

01:22:55.083 --> 01:22:56.417
I did. They're coming.

01:22:56.417 --> 01:22:58.250
(grunt)

01:22:58.250 --> 01:22:59.417
(grunt)

01:22:59.417 --> 01:23:00.292
(grunt)

01:23:00.292 --> 01:23:03.375
(panting)

01:23:03.375 --> 01:23:04.458
It's OK!

01:23:05.708 --> 01:23:07.875
Oh, my God!

01:23:07.875 --> 01:23:10.208
Oh, my God, Mom!

01:23:10.208 --> 01:23:11.833
It's OK, baby, it's over.

01:23:11.833 --> 01:23:14.542
(gasping)

01:23:14.542 --> 01:23:24.083
(sirens wailing)

01:23:29.542 --> 01:23:33.542
You know, I watch a lot of
comic-book movies with my kids.

01:23:33.542 --> 01:23:35.667
But I gotta say, you two
make a really great

01:23:35.667 --> 01:23:37.542
mother-daughter
superhero team.

01:23:37.542 --> 01:23:41.792
Uh, speaking of family, can
my dad come home now?

01:23:41.792 --> 01:23:43.917
I mean, based on this evening, I
don't think there's a judge

01:23:43.917 --> 01:23:47.208
in the country who would try to
keep your dad in custody.

01:23:47.208 --> 01:23:49.000
By the way, I'm going
to need you both

01:23:49.000 --> 01:23:50.375
to come downtown tomorrow.

01:23:50.375 --> 01:23:53.042
We're gonna need the whole story
on this Mr. Brad Collins.

01:23:53.042 --> 01:23:54.542
With pleasure!

01:23:54.542 --> 01:23:55.458
OK.

01:23:55.458 --> 01:24:05.417
♪

01:24:10.458 --> 01:24:11.375
♪

01:24:11.375 --> 01:24:12.292
Lucy, honey!

01:24:15.750 --> 01:24:18.208
Ah, Luce!

01:24:18.208 --> 01:24:20.208
Oh, look at you!

01:24:20.208 --> 01:24:21.042
Let's get some pictures.

01:24:21.042 --> 01:24:22.625
OK. (laugh)

01:24:22.625 --> 01:24:24.917
Oh, my goodness. You are too
grown up!

01:24:24.917 --> 01:24:26.083
(laughs) OK.

01:24:26.083 --> 01:24:27.208
All right, all right.

01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:30.167
(sigh) You look beautiful.

01:24:30.167 --> 01:24:31.333
Mm, thanks, Mom.

01:24:31.333 --> 01:24:32.750
Mm, OK.

01:24:35.958 --> 01:24:39.042
Hi!

01:24:39.042 --> 01:24:41.708
Oh, honey.

01:24:41.708 --> 01:24:44.792
Special delivery for the
two most beautiful...

01:24:44.792 --> 01:24:47.458
and brave women that
I know.

01:24:47.458 --> 01:24:49.208
Aw, thanks, Dad.

01:24:49.208 --> 01:24:50.542
You're welcome.

01:24:50.542 --> 01:24:52.500
So, just so you both
know, after the ceremony,

01:24:52.500 --> 01:24:55.375
I plan to go partying with
Madison and friends.

01:24:55.375 --> 01:24:58.375
Oh, well. In that
case, Sarah Watts,

01:24:58.375 --> 01:25:00.625
I'd like to ask you
out on a date.

01:25:00.625 --> 01:25:02.083
Like a first date?

01:25:02.083 --> 01:25:03.542
Yeah, like a first date.

01:25:09.625 --> 01:25:11.125
OK, I love this,

01:25:11.125 --> 01:25:12.458
but the ceremony's starting
really soon. (laugh)

01:25:12.458 --> 01:25:13.042
Oh!

01:25:13.042 --> 01:25:14.708
Right.

01:25:14.708 --> 01:25:19.667
Sorry, let me put these down
and uh, my purse... Sorry!

01:25:19.667 --> 01:25:20.833
Did you warm up the car?

01:25:20.833 --> 01:25:22.417
It's ready! It's ready!
